Dialogue: 0,0:00:15.78,0:00:24.71,Default,,0,0,0,,We shall resume the question is if there is no personal self, how do phenomena come about?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:26.14,0:00:28.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, they come about spontaneously
Dialogue: 0,0:00:29.44,0:00:34.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Through the process not of evolution or causation but through emergence
Dialogue: 0,0:00:35.29,0:00:38.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Which the science is reasonably caught up with?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:40.97,0:00:47.00,Default,,0,0,0,,but because of the evolutionary nature of the universe and of human life
Dialogue: 0,0:00:47.00,0:00:53.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Potentiality becomes actuality when local conditions are favorable
Dialogue: 0,0:00:54.43,0:00:58.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, it comes about and of course, we'll have a slide just quickly reviewing
Dialogue: 0,0:00:59.32,0:01:02.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Advanced theoretical physics, which you're all dying to know about
Dialogue: 0,0:01:05.31,0:01:07.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Mindful universe just came out Henry Stapp
Dialogue: 0,0:01:08.73,0:01:14.82,Default,,0,0,0,,It was available off the internet now. It's available as a book and the prices come down and it's quite reasonable now
Dialogue: 0,0:01:15.84,0:01:18.68,Default,,0,0,0,,For those that really want to understand better than
Dialogue: 0,0:01:19.23,0:01:22.48,Default,,0,0,0,,mathematics
Dialogue: 0,0:01:22.48,0:01:25.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Potentiality emerges then so
Dialogue: 0,0:01:26.01,0:01:30.56,Default,,0,0,0,,The idea of a personal self is the big barrier to enlightenment
Dialogue: 0,0:01:31.37,0:01:36.17,Default,,0,0,0,,The presumption that there is a personal self making all decisions
Dialogue: 0,0:01:37.51,0:01:38.51,Default,,0,0,0,,and
Dialogue: 0,0:01:38.51,0:01:46.29,Default,,0,0,0,,That this arm just went that way because I decided it. I didn't decide it. I didn't even think about it
Dialogue: 0,0:01:46.71,0:01:50.93,Default,,0,0,0,,It happened of its own. Let's see it does it again. Let's stop that
Dialogue: 0,0:01:51.45,0:01:55.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Put this thing away. All right
Dialogue: 0,0:01:55.15,0:02:02.95,Default,,0,0,0,,It goes out and waves like that. If you don't watch it. I say you just see what it does. It does it by itself
Dialogue: 0,0:02:06.82,0:02:09.44,Default,,0,0,0,,One day you'll catch you'll catch it you'll catch
Dialogue: 0,0:02:10.03,0:02:17.50,Default,,0,0,0,,That the phenomena are occurring independent of any personal decision. There isn't any personal you
Dialogue: 0,0:02:18.52,0:02:20.52,Default,,0,0,0,,making decisions and
Dialogue: 0,0:02:20.78,0:02:23.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Etc. There is no personal self
Dialogue: 0,0:02:23.59,0:02:28.15,Default,,0,0,0,,So long as you believe that there's a personal self making these decisions
Dialogue: 0,0:02:28.80,0:02:31.30,Default,,0,0,0,,You will then have to take karmic responsibility for them
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.87,0:02:34.59,Default,,0,0,0,,You be at the subject of Karma
Dialogue: 0,0:02:35.28,0:02:37.65,Default,,0,0,0,,And the Buddha warned against it
Dialogue: 0,0:02:41.71,0:02:45.02,Default,,0,0,0,,The Buddha warned against it you see if you
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.21,0:02:53.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Choose you humaness and then you have to take the Karma that goes within goes with humanness
Dialogue: 0,0:02:54.33,0:02:56.25,Default,,0,0,0,,and so this is a
Dialogue: 0,0:02:56.25,0:03:02.09,Default,,0,0,0,,And so the Buddha recommended to avoid reincarnating
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.09,0:03:07.28,Default,,0,0,0,,because you will reincarnate into the world of suffering, sickness, old age, and death.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.19,0:03:10.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Poverty, sickness, suffering, old age, and death.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.03,0:03:14.41,Default,,0,0,0,,The Buddha sounds a little bit like a pessimist, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.24,0:03:18.52,Default,,0,0,0,,He never met anybody that won the lottery
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.52,0:03:23.90,Default,,0,0,0,,or met a lovely woman and got to marry her and everything like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.90,0:03:29.71,Default,,0,0,0,,But the Buddha sort of had a stringent view of human life.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.84,0:03:33.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, it's because he was naive and protected from the realities of life.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.50,0:03:37.71,Default,,0,0,0,,And then he got away from his parents somehow and wandered into town
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.71,0:03:41.34,Default,,0,0,0,,and he saw old people, sickness, poverty, and death.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.49,0:03:43.99,Default,,0,0,0,,And he never got over the trauma of that.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.31,0:03:45.49,Default,,0,0,0,,He needed psychotherapy.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.99,0:03:53.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Old age, sickness, poverty, and death, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.34,0:03:56.03,Default,,0,0,0,,To avoid the...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.03,0:03:56.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Negative karma.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.15,0:04:01.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, boy, he recommended that you not reincarnate in the human domain.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.87,0:04:08.08,Default,,0,0,0,,And the way you do that is by not having either attractions or aversions.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.30,0:04:10.13,Default,,0,0,0,,And no attractions and no aversions.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.94,0:04:15.21,Default,,0,0,0,,So for whatever it's worth, we salute the Buddha.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.44,0:04:18.18,Default,,0,0,0,,And however, we're all here.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.26,0:04:18.94,Default,,0,0,0,,I noticed that.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.73,0:04:24.79,Default,,0,0,0,,I guess we didn't take him too seriously in the previous lifetime.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.76,0:04:29.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, I can hear us singing.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.37,0:04:31.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, the Buddha, that old fogey.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.02,0:04:34.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Who listens to him anyway?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.97,0:04:43.82,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, so there we are back in the world which modern academia is now ignoring.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.82,0:04:49.32,Default,,0,0,0,,And I won't go into my rant and raving about modern academia
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.32,0:04:51.08,Default,,0,0,0,,because I've already done that in previous lectures.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.82,0:04:57.61,Default,,0,0,0,,But the fact that academia has deserted,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.14,0:05:01.32,Default,,0,0,0,,the world of intellectual integrity,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.02,0:05:07.64,Default,,0,0,0,,of course, is why it's now sinking in the sinking ship of relativism.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.11,0:05:10.54,Default,,0,0,0,,With the exception of community colleges
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.54,0:05:14.42,Default,,0,0,0,,and places who are still calibrated in the mid-400s.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.54,0:05:16.51,Default,,0,0,0,,But the great universities in the East,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.60,0:05:17.69,Default,,0,0,0,,the great fabled names,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.27,0:05:19.56,Default,,0,0,0,,have all sunk below 200.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.92,0:05:23.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Can you believe the greatest names in Eastern great universities
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.95,0:05:25.89,Default,,0,0,0,,calibrate below 200?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.10,0:05:26.68,Default,,0,0,0,,It's unbelievable.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.92,0:05:27.33,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm saying myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.22,0:05:31.63,Default,,0,0,0,,I have permission to ask this.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.50,0:05:33.25,Default,,0,0,0,,That's a fact.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.39,0:05:33.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Resist.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.81,0:05:36.60,Default,,0,0,0,,I wish she was lying, but she's not.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.57,0:05:42.77,Default,,0,0,0,,The great universities with the great fabled names
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.77,0:05:47.72,Default,,0,0,0,,have been taken over by politically correct supervisors
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.72,0:05:50.01,Default,,0,0,0,,to make sure that they calibrate below 200.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.12,0:05:53.39,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, so that's what the Pope said.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.39,0:05:58.01,Default,,0,0,0,,The fall of Western civilization is due to two things.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.58,0:06:03.52,Default,,0,0,0,,One, the inroads of Islam, which have destroyed Europe,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.52,0:06:09.41,Default,,0,0,0,,and relativism, which is destroying the United States and academia.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.97,0:06:13.64,Default,,0,0,0,,However, so the best place to send your people say,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.79,0:06:15.32,Default,,0,0,0,,where should I send my kids?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.23,0:06:19.99,Default,,0,0,0,,I think in some recent book they gave a list of all the universities
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.99,0:06:21.82,Default,,0,0,0,,that are still calibrated in the 400s.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.41,0:06:26.32,Default,,0,0,0,,And community colleges calibrate in the 400s.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.32,0:06:30.14,Default,,0,0,0,,So the safest place to send your kid is the community college.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.17,0:06:34.61,Default,,0,0,0,,And if he goes to Yale or Harvard, pray, pray.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.61,0:06:41.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.25,0:06:42.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Because they have the prestige.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.68,0:06:46.37,Default,,0,0,0,,That's why the political left headed for them.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.76,0:06:48.75,Default,,0,0,0,,They headed for those that have the most prestige.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.76,0:06:52.52,Default,,0,0,0,,And so the community college is where you want to go.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.38,0:06:56.18,Default,,0,0,0,,And we can personally recommend them.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.38,0:06:57.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Can we recommend them?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.89,0:06:59.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Stand up and recommend them.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.31,0:07:12.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Then when you go to Calabria's in 440,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.55,0:07:15.38,Default,,0,0,0,,when he goes to Calabria, it's 440.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.76,0:07:17.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Right now, Yale and Harvard, I think Calabria at 190.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.64,0:07:22.06,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, so it's because you've deserted
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.06,0:07:25.11,Default,,0,0,0,,the greatest accomplishments of mankind.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.50,0:07:29.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Intellectual integrity, you know,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.18,0:07:33.92,Default,,0,0,0,,historically goes back to ancient someplace, rather.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.75,0:07:40.47,Default,,0,0,0,,The ancient Greeks, of course.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.47,0:07:42.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Athens and Plato and Aristotle.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.35,0:07:47.81,Default,,0,0,0,,And Socrates, these are the great, the great minds of history.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.97,0:07:54.31,Default,,0,0,0,,And so you ignore them at your own peril.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.17,0:07:56.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Because this is integrity.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.58,0:08:01.50,Default,,0,0,0,,And when you desert integrity, what happens is you fall into non-integrity.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.58,0:08:09.17,Default,,0,0,0,,So evolution is also doesn't mean it's progressive, progressively positive.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.64,0:08:10.79,Default,,0,0,0,,It goes through dips.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.79,0:08:12.23,Default,,0,0,0,,And we see that mankind.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.51,0:08:14.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Recently.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.12,0:08:14.22,Default,,0,0,0,,The.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.22,0:08:19.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Consciousness level of mankind, which was up to 207, has dropped down to 204.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.37,0:08:27.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Consciousness level of mankind was up to 207 and is now down to 204.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.52,0:08:28.62,Default,,0,0,0,,It's at 204.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.23,0:08:29.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.58,0:08:29.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.79,0:08:33.07,Default,,0,0,0,,So as I said, we were disappointed.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.07,0:08:38.21,Default,,0,0,0,,We thought evolution was going to keep going forward and instead it took a downturn.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.25,0:08:41.59,Default,,0,0,0,,So that's apparently the nature of evolution.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.59,0:08:42.88,Default,,0,0,0,,It comes, it fluctuates.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:42.88,0:08:44.35,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not just a smooth ride.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.15,0:08:45.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh huh.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.98,0:08:52.30,Default,,0,0,0,,So we can't just lay back then and figure that, well, all we have to do is depend on
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.30,0:08:57.78,Default,,0,0,0,,the evolution of consciousness and we're all going to be fine, uh, because that's not so.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.01,0:09:00.32,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.32,0:09:01.70,Default,,0,0,0,,So we'll, we'll move on.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.70,0:09:03.20,Default,,0,0,0,,All of those are the great names.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.69,0:09:09.54,Default,,0,0,0,,The difference between, um, perception and essence has to do with context and content.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.46,0:09:18.20,Default,,0,0,0,,So here we have an event and here's the content in a situation and the perceived event is, is, uh,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.20,0:09:21.29,Default,,0,0,0,,occurring within, uh, the linear domain.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.89,0:09:24.55,Default,,0,0,0,,The situation, however, is nonlinear.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.30,0:09:31.90,Default,,0,0,0,,So the context is event of event is the context in which it happens.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.61,0:09:41.02,Default,,0,0,0,,So much argumentation that goes on in politics and economics, et cetera of what's the right move to make.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.25,0:09:44.21,Default,,0,0,0,,It all depends on the situation.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.33,0:09:51.35,Default,,0,0,0,,So what a thing is depends not only on content, but context.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.76,0:09:59.33,Default,,0,0,0,,And the content includes the overall situation, including even the world situation.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.55,0:10:08.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Is it all right to check out what's that security thing right now hung up in Congress that can't get it approved?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.37,0:10:11.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway, the idea is to protect the lives of Americans.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.37,0:10:18.52,Default,,0,0,0,,So is it an infringement of human liberty or is it a safeguard of human liberty?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.52,0:10:24.04,Default,,0,0,0,,It all depends on how you view the context, how you view the context.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.12,0:10:28.15,Default,,0,0,0,,I myself don't care if they listen in on my phone conversations.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.91,0:10:34.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Can't you hear the government pouring all these people with these things on banks of them, buildings of them listening in?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.34,0:10:37.24,Default,,0,0,0,,And then what did you put in after the mustard?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.37,0:10:38.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Did you fry it?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.94,0:10:46.20,Default,,0,0,0,,You say there's testicles in there, we should take them to the doctor?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.20,0:10:54.16,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, rows and rows of Secret Service listening to this with earphones.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.75,0:10:58.97,Default,,0,0,0,,The government's listening to me, baby.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.61,0:11:02.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, better watch your mouth.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.23,0:11:04.12,Default,,0,0,0,,There, that's what I say.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.87,0:11:09.12,Default,,0,0,0,,You're worried about the government listening to your conversation, watch what you say.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.46,0:11:12.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Send the telegram.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.77,0:11:13.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Go ahead.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.24,0:11:13.84,Default,,0,0,0,,What's the next one?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.03,0:11:16.46,Default,,0,0,0,,What's the next slide?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.17,0:11:17.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.87,0:11:25.35,Default,,0,0,0,,So we talk about, we differentiate the context, the overall context, the spirit, the time, the age, the era.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.96,0:11:27.89,Default,,0,0,0,,The political system.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.00,0:11:30.05,Default,,0,0,0,,The situation, the financial situation.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.27,0:11:35.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Before you make up a decision, then.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.44,0:11:38.36,Default,,0,0,0,,The content is just not Newtonian and measurable at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.48,0:11:40.32,Default,,0,0,0,,It depends on the circumstances.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.25,0:11:43.65,Default,,0,0,0,,It depends on the proximate field.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.60,0:11:47.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Is the country at war or not at war?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.70,0:11:48.13,Default,,0,0,0,,You understand?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.32,0:11:50.34,Default,,0,0,0,,That makes all the difference in the world, doesn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.50,0:11:55.20,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, you can't draft people when the world is not at war.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.48,0:11:57.77,Default,,0,0,0,,You can hardly, hard enough to draft them when it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:57.86,0:11:58.25,Default,,0,0,0,,You know what I'm saying?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.25,0:11:58.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.24,0:12:00.25,Default,,0,0,0,,So the overall.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.17,0:12:04.27,Default,,0,0,0,,The overall context is what gives meaning.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.46,0:12:08.87,Default,,0,0,0,,So there's truth as content, depending on context.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.32,0:12:13.84,Default,,0,0,0,,But then, out of content and context, you derive meaning.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.27,0:12:21.34,Default,,0,0,0,,So beyond literal content and the context in which it happens is meaning.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.09,0:12:27.24,Default,,0,0,0,,And that is not understood by the public at large.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.32,0:12:30.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Is it legal to do that?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.13,0:12:31.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, it depends on the situation.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.99,0:12:33.73,Default,,0,0,0,,But what I want to know.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.73,0:12:35.71,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, is, well, so what does that mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.87,0:12:38.05,Default,,0,0,0,,What does that mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.29,0:12:40.87,Default,,0,0,0,,What it means is what's significant.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.46,0:12:43.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Not the event, not the circumstances.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.13,0:12:45.36,Default,,0,0,0,,But what's the meaning of that?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.51,0:12:47.58,Default,,0,0,0,,What was the Boston Tea Party?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.67,0:12:48.89,Default,,0,0,0,,What was the meaning of that?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.07,0:12:51.45,Default,,0,0,0,,They dumped tea in the ocean?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.82,0:12:53.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Is that all there was to it?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.20,0:12:55.24,Default,,0,0,0,,No, that was a protest.
