Dialogue: 0,0:25:48.64,0:25:55.27,Default,,0,0,0,,The sheep or dog comes from comparable right brain, feels responsible.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:56.24,0:25:59.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Wherever I go around the house, the dog has to check, where are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:00.43,0:26:02.30,Default,,0,0,0,,The missus goes in the other room.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:02.30,0:26:04.30,Default,,0,0,0,,She goes and checks where is the missus.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:04.30,0:26:07.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Then she has to come back and check where I am.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:07.30,0:26:09.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Then she has to see where the cats are.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:10.30,0:26:12.30,Default,,0,0,0,,By that time, it's time to go and check where the missus is again.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:13.75,0:26:18.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Then she's got to go and see if Gabe is here yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:18.43,0:26:24.93,Default,,0,0,0,,That keeping trackness is somehow very heartwarming, you know, the heartwarmingness, it's almost
Dialogue: 0,0:26:24.93,0:26:29.52,Default,,0,0,0,,like a maternal instinct, it's almost like a maternal instinct that has to watch all
Dialogue: 0,0:26:29.52,0:26:32.73,Default,,0,0,0,,the children and make sure that they're all okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:33.41,0:26:34.73,Default,,0,0,0,,When you take a baby, it doesn't work.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:34.73,0:26:35.73,Default,,0,0,0,,It has to stay there.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:35.73,0:26:36.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Get a baby.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:36.73,0:26:37.82,Default,,0,0,0,,When you're in a stupor and it has to feel good, it has to be in a good mood.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:37.82,0:26:38.82,Default,,0,0,0,,That's important.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:38.82,0:26:39.82,Default,,0,0,0,,It has to feel good.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:39.82,0:26:41.52,Default,,0,0,0,,It's important to get it right, and I'm the kind of person who'll take every little
Dialogue: 0,0:26:41.52,0:26:42.52,Default,,0,0,0,,little thing, you know, off the hook for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:42.52,0:26:52.17,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a little bit of a surgery, a little bit of a
Dialogue: 0,0:26:52.17,0:26:53.17,Default,,0,0,0,,surgery.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:53.17,0:26:54.17,Default,,0,0,0,,That's a good rule of thumb, as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:54.17,0:26:55.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, it has to feel like it's been through that all the time, just like we had with
Dialogue: 0,0:26:55.35,0:26:56.35,Default,,0,0,0,,our daughter, we had her in the car.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:56.35,0:26:57.35,Default,,0,0,0,,She's still happy.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:57.35,0:26:58.35,Default,,0,0,0,,She's still going.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:58.35,0:26:59.61,Default,,0,0,0,,And I think it's a good thing that she's a little bit more of that Meadow- dies.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:59.61,0:27:03.44,Default,,0,0,0,,We had a model way forward where the top was down, you know, so we're driving along.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:03.92,0:27:05.92,Default,,0,0,0,,And I took the Gaga and I threw it over the side.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:06.74,0:27:09.83,Default,,0,0,0,,And my father had to put the brake on and back up to get the Gaga.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:10.53,0:27:11.50,Default,,0,0,0,,So that was fun.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:11.50,0:27:18.35,Default,,0,0,0,,So a couple of miles farther down, I threw the Gaga over the side again.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:19.45,0:27:24.19,Default,,0,0,0,,And my father had to put the brake on and back up and get the Gaga again.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:24.98,0:27:28.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Then he said, if you do that one more time, I'm not going to go back for it.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:28.38,0:27:30.30,Default,,0,0,0,,And I giggled.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:31.74,0:27:33.40,Default,,0,0,0,,So I did it one more time.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:38.48,0:27:39.59,Default,,0,0,0,,So that's what I mean.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:39.61,0:27:41.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't fool around with God.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:43.32,0:27:48.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Give him two shots, but on the third shot, you better watch your butt, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:50.06,0:27:53.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Because he may not back up and get your Gaga the third time.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:59.04,0:28:04.23,Default,,0,0,0,,So that's the lesson of Gaga land.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:05.04,0:28:05.26,Default,,0,0,0,,And.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:05.45,0:28:07.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Which side of the brain you want to live on.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:07.13,0:28:09.10,Default,,0,0,0,,OK, so let's move to the next side of the brain.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:09.28,0:28:16.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, this has to do with a sort of in a way it contradicts a lot of social theories.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:17.51,0:28:22.55,Default,,0,0,0,,You see, the Marxian dialectic, they divide everything into perpetrator and victim.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:23.16,0:28:30.44,Default,,0,0,0,,And then it projects perpetrator is always society and victim is always some minority until they become the majority.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:30.44,0:28:31.55,Default,,0,0,0,,And then they switch sides.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:32.98,0:28:36.53,Default,,0,0,0,,But anyway, for a period of time, everybody gets to be in the minority.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:38.55,0:28:38.79,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:38.81,0:28:47.49,Default,,0,0,0,,So it says all these things such as rate of unemployment, poverty, happiness, criminality are all due to society.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:47.49,0:28:53.75,Default,,0,0,0,,It's society's fault that you cheat on your classwork or whatever you do.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:54.70,0:28:55.01,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:55.09,0:29:01.74,Default,,0,0,0,,So the research we did shows that, no, it's really related to that which you really are.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:03.15,0:29:08.93,Default,,0,0,0,,These social problems are really problems of the consequences.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:08.93,0:29:16.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Of levels of consciousness, the lower levels of consciousness have everything wrong with them, 50 to 100.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:16.89,0:29:19.04,Default,,0,0,0,,This is the usual prison population.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:20.38,0:29:22.07,Default,,0,0,0,,This is the prison population.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:23.83,0:29:29.96,Default,,0,0,0,,The recidivism in these kinds of prison populations is almost 100 percent.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:30.14,0:29:38.53,Default,,0,0,0,,The likelihood of you getting out of jail for robbery, the likelihood is close to 100 percent that you'll be back again before very long.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:38.53,0:29:40.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:40.56,0:29:47.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Because, and the reason you can't learn from experience is because your consciousness level is down here.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:48.15,0:29:51.21,Default,,0,0,0,,The rate of unemployment here is practically 100 percent.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:52.03,0:29:56.24,Default,,0,0,0,,The rate of poverty is a majority.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:57.31,0:30:00.09,Default,,0,0,0,,How many of these people think life is okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:00.27,0:30:01.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Close to zero percent.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:01.81,0:30:05.16,Default,,0,0,0,,And those that think it's okay is only because they're stoned at the moment.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:07.83,0:30:10.38,Default,,0,0,0,,The rate of criminality is close to 100 percent.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:10.38,0:30:15.23,Default,,0,0,0,,So, you know, it's a lot of work.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:15.23,0:30:24.47,Default,,0,0,0,,So, this has great significance in our judicial system, prison system, and an understanding of these things might give us some hope.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:25.64,0:30:29.51,Default,,0,0,0,,I forget what percent of the United States population has more than any country.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:29.83,0:30:33.14,Default,,0,0,0,,The United States has more people in jail or prison than any country in the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:34.39,0:30:35.13,Default,,0,0,0,,More than anybody.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:35.65,0:30:37.99,Default,,0,0,0,,We've got 3 percent or 1 percent, I forget what it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:38.80,0:30:41.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway, more people in prison in the United States.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:41.75,0:30:42.69,Default,,0,0,0,,This is the land of freedom.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:42.69,0:30:45.69,Default,,0,0,0,,And, of course, that's pointed out to be critical of us.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:45.69,0:30:50.28,Default,,0,0,0,,The land of freedom has more people in prison than all the other countries in the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:51.23,0:30:53.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Could be we have better police, that's why.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:57.25,0:30:59.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Because you kill somebody, nobody gives a rap.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:00.04,0:31:00.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Here they care.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:00.76,0:31:01.63,Default,,0,0,0,,They arrest you and everything.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:01.76,0:31:02.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Put you in prison.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:03.50,0:31:03.72,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:03.85,0:31:11.66,Default,,0,0,0,,So, the rate of, you see, all these sociologic problems are really not due to some causality out there.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:12.31,0:31:15.11,Default,,0,0,0,,They're due to what you have become in here.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:15.31,0:31:16.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Just.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:16.14,0:31:20.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Consciousness, happiness is a consequence of what you have become within yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:21.88,0:31:27.70,Default,,0,0,0,,That, the opposite of it, is also a consequence of what you have learned, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:28.35,0:31:36.50,Default,,0,0,0,,So, people who are the so-called psychopath ridicules all the things that spiritual work stands for.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:36.59,0:31:39.42,Default,,0,0,0,,All the things that we consider the most valuable.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:39.42,0:31:45.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Self-sacrifice, service to others, love, respect for divinity, etc.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:46.14,0:31:46.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Are ridiculed.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:47.44,0:31:47.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:47.81,0:31:48.59,Default,,0,0,0,,So, we'll go to the next.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:50.75,0:31:52.84,Default,,0,0,0,,The rate of happiness, here you see.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:53.76,0:31:57.69,Default,,0,0,0,,So, we said the rate of happiness is not a sociologic condition.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:58.39,0:32:01.56,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a consequence of that which you have become.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:02.83,0:32:15.67,Default,,0,0,0,,People who live down here, down here, the percent of people happy in shame, guilt, apathy, hatred, grief.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:16.34,0:32:17.65,Default,,0,0,0,,People who live in fear.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:17.76,0:32:23.64,Default,,0,0,0,,People who are constantly craving, wanting something.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:23.64,0:32:25.92,Default,,0,0,0,,People who are constantly angry.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:25.92,0:32:28.33,Default,,0,0,0,,And people who live out of pride.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:28.33,0:32:33.48,Default,,0,0,0,,You see that the great majority of those people are unhappy.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:33.48,0:32:38.15,Default,,0,0,0,,The rate of happiness suddenly jumps at level 200.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:38.15,0:32:46.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Below 200, about 22% of that is the most will say that they're happy.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:46.02,0:32:48.19,Default,,0,0,0,,That's probably because they're stoned.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:48.19,0:32:50.30,Default,,0,0,0,,And after the martini wears off, they will get.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:51.84,0:32:59.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway, from 200 and up, you suddenly see the percent of happiness jumps enormously.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:00.33,0:33:10.16,Default,,0,0,0,,So, the first benefit you get from a spiritual, integrous, ethical orientation towards life is a greater rate of happiness.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:10.44,0:33:12.46,Default,,0,0,0,,This comes from self-approval.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:13.43,0:33:15.06,Default,,0,0,0,,The inner knowingness.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:15.06,0:33:15.97,Default,,0,0,0,,The inner knowingness.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:16.08,0:33:17.06,Default,,0,0,0,,The meaning of your life.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:17.52,0:33:18.75,Default,,0,0,0,,So, the meaning of your life.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:18.75,0:33:20.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Is that your life is significant.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:20.75,0:33:22.75,Default,,0,0,0,,That you serve yourself and others.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:22.75,0:33:29.03,Default,,0,0,0,,And that you're helpful to the life of others and the enjoyment of life, the safety and security.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:29.03,0:33:35.03,Default,,0,0,0,,So, dedicating your life to ethics and integrity and truth, et cetera.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:35.03,0:33:37.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Has an immediate benefit.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:37.03,0:33:39.03,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't have to become enlightened.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:39.03,0:33:41.03,Default,,0,0,0,,All you have to do is get to be happier.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:43.03,0:33:45.03,Default,,0,0,0,,All you have to do is get to be happier.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:45.03,0:33:47.96,Default,,0,0,0,,So, I've never recommended the sackcloth and ashes type of life.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:47.96,0:33:51.27,Default,,0,0,0,,The sackcloth and ashes type of religiosity.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:51.27,0:33:56.27,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, Ramana Maharshi was a great teacher, et cetera.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:56.27,0:34:01.33,Default,,0,0,0,,But he lived in the Hindu tradition of asceticism.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:01.33,0:34:07.50,Default,,0,0,0,,And the more bent over and skinny, et cetera, that you got, the more holy you got.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:07.50,0:34:18.03,Default,,0,0,0,,It isn't necessary to starve yourself to death and live in a hut and live on grass and carbon dioxide or something.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:18.03,0:34:20.03,Default,,0,0,0,,The spiritual awareness happens independently.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:20.03,0:34:23.03,Default,,0,0,0,,It happens independently of all of that.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:23.03,0:34:26.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Not as a consequence of all that.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:26.11,0:34:27.73,Default,,0,0,0,,That's true.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:27.73,0:34:28.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Resist.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:28.73,0:34:31.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Sometimes.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:31.36,0:34:38.84,Default,,0,0,0,,You see, the westerner gets impressed by the more bizarre aspects of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:38.84,0:34:41.84,Default,,0,0,0,,I can take off all my clothes and you'll see I'm very skinny.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:41.84,0:34:53.15,Default,,0,0,0,,We can all take our clothes off and get very skinny.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:55.92,0:34:58.92,Default,,0,0,0,,But that is a side issue.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:58.92,0:35:01.05,Default,,0,0,0,,I just want to clarify that.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:01.05,0:35:09.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Some of the things in the spiritual literature, people focus on what is irrelevant, a side issue.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:09.05,0:35:18.05,Default,,0,0,0,,It's the dedication to service, to unconditional lovingness, to being all that you can be for the benefit of the world, you see.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:18.05,0:35:22.05,Default,,0,0,0,,And Ramana Maharshi loved all kinds of animals.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:22.05,0:35:27.05,Default,,0,0,0,,And he thought that the calves and the cows had souls.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:27.05,0:35:29.05,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know if a cow has a soul or not.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:29.05,0:35:32.51,Default,,0,0,0,,I have permission to ask this.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:32.51,0:35:34.75,Default,,0,0,0,,A cow has a soul.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:34.75,0:35:36.75,Default,,0,0,0,,He was right.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:36.75,0:35:40.94,Default,,0,0,0,,So does it have, it's like a cow's soul?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:40.94,0:35:41.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:41.94,0:35:43.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, it has its own animal soul.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:43.94,0:35:45.94,Default,,0,0,0,,And that's why we picked up Kelsey.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:45.94,0:35:46.94,Default,,0,0,0,,We just looked at this dog.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:46.94,0:35:49.94,Default,,0,0,0,,This one dog radiated out from a whole bunch of them.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:49.94,0:35:53.94,Default,,0,0,0,,And you just felt the heart energy radiate out.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:53.94,0:35:55.51,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:55.51,0:36:02.71,Default,,0,0,0,,So we can love the animals and realize they have their own animal souls and love them for what they are.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:02.71,0:36:08.71,Default,,0,0,0,,So a truly evolved person tends to be loving towards all of life and all of its expressions.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:08.71,0:36:21.09,Default,,0,0,0,,The beautiful flowers, the rabbits hopping along, the squirrels in the tree, the cows munching away, the horses, and the cats and the dogs and the birds flying around.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:21.09,0:36:24.15,Default,,0,0,0,,So you tend to love life in all of its expressions.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:24.15,0:36:27.15,Default,,0,0,0,,You tend to love life in all its expressions.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:27.15,0:36:29.15,Default,,0,0,0,,All of its expressions.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:29.15,0:36:32.51,Default,,0,0,0,,So the spiritually evolved person loves life in all of its expressions.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:32.51,0:36:34.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Loves life in all of its expressions.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:34.51,0:36:35.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Resists.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:35.63,0:36:36.63,Default,,0,0,0,,All of its expressions.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:36.63,0:36:40.07,Default,,0,0,0,,And you can't really do that unless you have a sense of humor.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:40.07,0:36:42.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Can't really do that without a sense of humor.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:42.34,0:36:43.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Resists.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:43.34,0:36:44.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Right.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:44.34,0:36:49.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Because you have no other way, no way to contextualize that which appears to be its opposite, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:49.34,0:36:51.23,Default,,0,0,0,,What appears to be it.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:51.23,0:36:55.23,Default,,0,0,0,,So the sense of humor is a very valuable spiritual tool.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:55.23,0:37:00.75,Default,,0,0,0,,And it should be represented more than it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:00.75,0:37:04.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Without a sense of humor, you can't feel compassionate towards many things.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:04.00,0:37:05.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Right.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:05.00,0:37:06.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Without a sense of humor, you can't feel compassionate towards many things.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:06.00,0:37:12.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Once you recontextualize it and see the humor of it, you can see the humanness of that,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:12.00,0:37:13.00,Default,,0,0,0,,then it's okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:13.00,0:37:18.13,Default,,0,0,0,,You can say, yeah, I don't believe it, but I can understand why people are that way.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:18.13,0:37:20.13,Default,,0,0,0,,That allows you to include it in.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:20.13,0:37:22.13,Default,,0,0,0,,So that's the great value of humor.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:22.13,0:37:25.13,Default,,0,0,0,,The humorists all live to be very old, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:25.13,0:37:31.13,Default,,0,0,0,,The classic humorists almost all live into their 90s, just as the classical musicians
Dialogue: 0,0:37:31.13,0:37:34.15,Default,,0,0,0,,and composers and concert conductors, etc.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:34.15,0:37:37.28,Default,,0,0,0,,They used to live well into their 90s.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:37.28,0:37:42.28,Default,,0,0,0,,And so does, what was it, George Burns was, what, 99 when he finally fell over?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:42.28,0:37:47.48,Default,,0,0,0,,So the way to live long is to love music and be funny.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:52.01,0:37:53.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Enjoy humor.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:53.01,0:37:54.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Value humor.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:54.01,0:37:55.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Value humor.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:55.01,0:37:58.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Learn how to see the humorous side of life, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:58.01,0:38:01.01,Default,,0,0,0,,The paradoxes of life are very comical.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:01.01,0:38:02.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you see what I'm saying?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:02.01,0:38:03.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:03.01,0:38:04.36,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:04.36,0:38:05.36,Default,,0,0,0,,So the rate of happiness.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:05.36,0:38:09.71,Default,,0,0,0,,We're concerned with being happy.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:09.71,0:38:10.71,Default,,0,0,0,,I want everybody to be happy.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:10.71,0:38:15.19,Default,,0,0,0,,I insist that they be happy.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:15.19,0:38:18.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Anybody here not want to be happy?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:18.61,0:38:19.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Come on.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:19.96,0:38:20.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Guys up.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:20.96,0:38:22.96,Default,,0,0,0,,I know you're hiding there.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:22.96,0:38:24.59,Default,,0,0,0,,I see you there.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:24.59,0:38:25.59,Default,,0,0,0,,I see you.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:25.59,0:38:29.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Come up here.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:29.98,0:38:30.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Just gave up.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:30.98,0:38:31.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Decided he wanted to be happy.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:31.98,0:38:32.98,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:32.98,0:38:34.80,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:34.80,0:38:35.80,Default,,0,0,0,,So the rate of happiness then.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:35.80,0:38:39.96,Default,,0,0,0,,So even if you don't become enlightened, the trip is a wonderful trip.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:39.96,0:38:40.96,Default,,0,0,0,,You'll enjoy life much more.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:40.96,0:38:41.96,Default,,0,0,0,,You'll get more gratification and fulfillment by becoming the completion and fulfillment
Dialogue: 0,0:38:41.96,0:38:42.96,Default,,0,0,0,,of that which you are.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:42.96,0:38:43.96,Default,,0,0,0,,And so we grow through the heart.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:43.96,0:38:44.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Through the heart.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:44.96,0:38:45.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:45.96,0:38:46.96,Default,,0,0,0,,The next.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:46.96,0:38:47.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:47.96,0:38:48.96,Default,,0,0,0,,So spirituality is really the way of the heart.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:48.96,0:38:49.96,Default,,0,0,0,,The way of the heart.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:49.96,0:38:50.96,Default,,0,0,0,,We add the world of the intellect.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:50.96,0:38:51.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, how did that get in there?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:51.96,0:38:52.96,Default,,0,0,0,,I haven't seen those in a long time.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:52.96,0:38:53.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's go back and get them.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:53.96,0:38:54.96,Default,,0,0,0,,What was that one?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:54.96,0:38:56.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:56.03,0:38:57.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:57.03,0:38:58.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:58.73,0:38:59.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:59.73,0:39:00.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:00.73,0:39:01.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:01.73,0:39:02.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:02.80,0:39:03.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:03.80,0:39:04.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:04.80,0:39:05.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:05.80,0:39:07.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
