Dialogue: 0,0:39:10.92,0:39:11.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:11.92,0:39:12.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Ooh.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:12.92,0:39:13.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, the .
Dialogue: 0,0:39:13.92,0:39:14.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:14.92,0:39:15.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, this.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:15.92,0:39:16.92,Default,,0,0,0,,No, wait a minute.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:16.92,0:39:17.96,Default,,0,0,0,,No, before that.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:17.96,0:39:18.96,Default,,0,0,0,,What was that one?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:18.96,0:39:19.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Is that one we're supposed to show?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:19.96,0:39:20.96,Default,,0,0,0,,The one before this one?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:20.96,0:39:22.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:22.78,0:39:25.44,Default,,0,0,0,,What's the last?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:25.44,0:39:26.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, what's 31.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:26.44,0:39:29.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:29.65,0:39:33.25,Default,,0,0,0,,No, the one before that.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:33.25,0:39:34.25,Default,,0,0,0,,There, there.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:34.25,0:39:36.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Hold that.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:36.78,0:39:37.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Hold that.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:37.78,0:39:38.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:38.78,0:39:39.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Hold that.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:39.78,0:39:41.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:41.40,0:39:42.40,Default,,0,0,0,,I know what this is.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:42.40,0:39:49.51,Default,,0,0,0,,This is the Application of Consciousness Research to International Relationships and International
Dialogue: 0,0:39:49.51,0:39:50.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Politics.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:50.51,0:39:51.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:51.78,0:40:00.26,Default,,0,0,0,,And you put together the level of consciousness scale, and you put where are you coming from,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:00.90,0:40:03.82,Default,,0,0,0,,what's the consciousness level, let's say, of the U.S.,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:03.82,0:40:07.23,Default,,0,0,0,,and what's the consciousness level that people were negotiating with.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:07.94,0:40:10.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, this is generally applicable.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:10.50,0:40:14.94,Default,,0,0,0,,You can do my business, my company, my anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:15.82,0:40:18.15,Default,,0,0,0,,And this is the community we're dealing with.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:18.15,0:40:20.84,Default,,0,0,0,,So here's the community, calibrates it so and so.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:21.78,0:40:26.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Our organization calibrates it this, so you can see what is necessary.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:29.13,0:40:37.11,Default,,0,0,0,,If you're at level 425, talking to somebody at level 75 is not going to make any sense to them
Dialogue: 0,0:40:37.11,0:40:39.75,Default,,0,0,0,,because you don't live in the same reality.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:40.53,0:40:44.73,Default,,0,0,0,,These people are worrying about staying alive until tomorrow with food and stuff like this,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:44.90,0:40:49.30,Default,,0,0,0,,and you're talking about democracy or something.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:49.42,0:40:51.71,Default,,0,0,0,,They think that's interesting, except you can't eat it.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:52.01,0:40:53.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, we'll go to the next slide.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:53.61,0:40:55.32,Default,,0,0,0,,You can't eat democracy, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:57.05,0:40:58.25,Default,,0,0,0,,You can only eat food.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:58.57,0:40:59.34,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll go to the next one.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:00.28,0:41:07.36,Default,,0,0,0,,It's better to have a dictator who gives you food than democracy with no food.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:07.46,0:41:08.13,Default,,0,0,0,,You understand what I'm saying?
Dialogue: 0,0:41:08.90,0:41:12.38,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, so let's go to the next slide, 33, 39.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:14.42,0:41:15.76,Default,,0,0,0,,We jump all over the place.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:15.84,0:41:16.15,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:17.55,0:41:19.59,Default,,0,0,0,,She's gone mad, the lady with the PowerPoint.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:21.96,0:41:22.90,Default,,0,0,0,,She's gone mad.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:22.90,0:41:27.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:27.86,0:41:28.76,Default,,0,0,0,,What was the next one I marked?
Dialogue: 0,0:41:29.80,0:41:30.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Did we do 33?
Dialogue: 0,0:41:31.34,0:41:31.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:36.94,0:41:38.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Consciousness rate of happiness.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:38.55,0:41:39.36,Default,,0,0,0,,We did that, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:41.73,0:41:42.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes?
Dialogue: 0,0:41:42.55,0:41:43.44,Default,,0,0,0,,International relationships.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:43.44,0:41:44.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, we did that one.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:44.21,0:41:45.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, so we're on the right one.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:45.21,0:41:45.96,Default,,0,0,0,,We're on the right track.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:46.13,0:41:47.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, my God, I'm relieved.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:47.23,0:41:48.32,Default,,0,0,0,,I thought we were on the wrong track.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:51.26,0:41:52.17,Default,,0,0,0,,This is the heaven track.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:52.28,0:41:54.03,Default,,0,0,0,,I thought we were on the other one maybe for a moment.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:54.59,0:41:57.80,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't want to aggravate the powers that be.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:58.13,0:42:02.78,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, this is something that we need to clarify.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:02.78,0:42:03.76,Default,,0,0,0,,What is the nature?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:03.76,0:42:05.26,Default,,0,0,0,,The nature of true spiritual teachers.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:06.53,0:42:09.67,Default,,0,0,0,,And because society is somewhat confused about this,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:10.59,0:42:14.05,Default,,0,0,0,,the nature of spiritual truth then,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:14.94,0:42:19.53,Default,,0,0,0,,if we study this, we'll find that spiritual truth is universally true
Dialogue: 0,0:42:19.53,0:42:21.15,Default,,0,0,0,,at all times and all places.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:21.34,0:42:25.51,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not dependent on being in New York City or California.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:27.00,0:42:28.30,Default,,0,0,0,,It's non-exclusive.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:28.78,0:42:29.86,Default,,0,0,0,,It's all-inclusive.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:29.86,0:42:34.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Non-sectarian and non-sectarian.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:34.09,0:42:37.44,Default,,0,0,0,,It's available, open to everybody.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:37.44,0:42:41.09,Default,,0,0,0,,So, you see, spiritual truth is open to everyone.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:41.42,0:42:42.96,Default,,0,0,0,,It doesn't cost anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:42.96,0:42:48.90,Default,,0,0,0,,There are no secrets to be revealed, hidden, sold, no magical formulas or mysteries.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:50.34,0:42:52.28,Default,,0,0,0,,The integrity is that of purpose.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:52.40,0:42:54.23,Default,,0,0,0,,There's nothing to gain or lose.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:55.23,0:42:59.55,Default,,0,0,0,,So, a spiritual teaching is what it is for its own sake.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:00.53,0:43:04.53,Default,,0,0,0,,It merely wants to share what it's learned for the benefit of everyone.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:04.53,0:43:11.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Truth is not the exposition of limitation, it's independent of opinion.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:12.92,0:43:21.46,Default,,0,0,0,,We say truth is non-linear and not subject to the limitations of reason or the intellect or form.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:23.34,0:43:26.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Truth is not anti-anything, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:26.07,0:43:31.30,Default,,0,0,0,,They all calibrate in the mid-300s, so we don't care who wins the election.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:31.30,0:43:33.90,Default,,0,0,0,,One side or the other one, they're all about the same.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:34.86,0:43:36.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Falsehood and ignorance are not.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:36.48,0:43:36.78,Default,,0,0,0,,It's ethical.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:36.78,0:43:39.46,Default,,0,0,0,,They're not enemies, but merely represent the absence of truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:40.32,0:43:42.69,Default,,0,0,0,,So, we're not anti-falsehood.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:43.34,0:43:46.53,Default,,0,0,0,,We just sort of bemoan the fact that the truth is missing.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:47.51,0:43:49.34,Default,,0,0,0,,There's no requirements or demands.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:49.61,0:43:54.71,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, there are many sects, you know, many demand all kinds of strange things.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:54.84,0:44:01.71,Default,,0,0,0,,You've got to eat weird things and eat just worms and shave your hair and do and chant and make strange sounds.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:03.15,0:44:06.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway, there are no requirements for membership.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:06.75,0:44:06.80,Default,,0,0,0,,There's no requirements for membership.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:06.80,0:44:07.11,Default,,0,0,0,,There's no requirements for membership.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:07.11,0:44:11.98,Default,,0,0,0,,There's no dues, there's no regulations, no oaths, no rules or conditions.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:13.48,0:44:18.78,Default,,0,0,0,,A true spiritual teacher has no interest in controlling the personal lives of aspirants,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:19.61,0:44:23.09,Default,,0,0,0,,telling them how to run their sex lives, et cetera.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:23.23,0:44:29.88,Default,,0,0,0,,A lot of times there's been some recent exposés even in local papers where I am, you know,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:30.01,0:44:34.25,Default,,0,0,0,,of denominations that do the exact opposite of all this.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:34.25,0:44:36.73,Default,,0,0,0,,And you say to yourself, how could anybody be so naive?
Dialogue: 0,0:44:37.59,0:44:41.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Tell you who to go to bed with and you have to get his permission in order to drive your car.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:42.80,0:44:46.11,Default,,0,0,0,,And it's very bizarre, the extremes.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:47.26,0:44:49.73,Default,,0,0,0,,And the head of the sect says that he's higher than God.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:51.96,0:44:53.05,Default,,0,0,0,,He's higher than God.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:53.32,0:44:53.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:56.36,0:44:58.17,Default,,0,0,0,,I'd like to meet somebody higher than God.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:58.42,0:45:06.55,Default,,0,0,0,,But, all right, so we don't tell people how to clothe, how to dress, their sex lives, their love life, their economics,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:06.55,0:45:09.55,Default,,0,0,0,,who they should go out with, who they should marry.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:09.67,0:45:10.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Et cetera.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:10.42,0:45:15.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Lifestyles or what they should eat or not eat, except if you eat a lot of sugar and sweets, be careful.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:19.19,0:45:20.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Free of force or intimidation.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:21.23,0:45:29.69,Default,,0,0,0,,There is no brainwashing, no adulation of great leader, no great leader, no training rituals,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:29.69,0:45:36.01,Default,,0,0,0,,indoctrinations, no intrusions into private life, adulations of great leaders.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:36.01,0:45:40.15,Default,,0,0,0,,There's countries in the world where the adulation of the great leader is, you know,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:40.17,0:45:43.57,Default,,0,0,0,,it's the whole, what holds the society together.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:44.40,0:45:46.53,Default,,0,0,0,,The great leader's picture is everywhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:47.00,0:45:49.67,Default,,0,0,0,,People worship great leader, great leader, great leader.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:50.53,0:45:54.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, when you calibrate great leader, I will not mention who great leader is.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:55.15,0:45:57.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Great leader calibrates over 200, he says.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:59.55,0:46:01.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Great leader doesn't even calibrate 200.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:02.78,0:46:04.88,Default,,0,0,0,,My dog calibrate to 255.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:04.88,0:46:09.90,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, bring Kelsey, you can worship Kelsey here.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:09.90,0:46:12.50,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, so.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:12.50,0:46:12.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Excuse me.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:12.73,0:46:17.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Great sacrifice in the name of then political power is oppression, oppression.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:19.00,0:46:21.03,Default,,0,0,0,,So you see how lucky our country is.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:21.13,0:46:24.96,Default,,0,0,0,,We bemoan it and criticize each other, and during political times like this,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:25.03,0:46:28.73,Default,,0,0,0,,people get nasty with each other and say horrible things.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:28.88,0:46:31.36,Default,,0,0,0,,But compared to other countries, our world is heavenly.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:32.07,0:46:34.92,Default,,0,0,0,,The most negative thing you can say about our political system
Dialogue: 0,0:46:34.92,0:46:37.80,Default,,0,0,0,,would be a heavenly gift in another culture, yeah?
Dialogue: 0,0:46:38.63,0:46:40.11,Default,,0,0,0,,So let's go to the next one.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:40.53,0:46:44.36,Default,,0,0,0,,In non-binding, you don't have to sign any contracts.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:44.46,0:46:51.23,Default,,0,0,0,,The reason I didn't join the prestigious organization,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:51.23,0:46:54.05,Default,,0,0,0,,all the men in my family belonged to it for generations.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:55.05,0:46:58.78,Default,,0,0,0,,And then it came my turn to become a member of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:59.40,0:47:03.30,Default,,0,0,0,,And I said, and I found out that you had to take an oath and swear by an oath.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:04.07,0:47:06.53,Default,,0,0,0,,And when I heard you had to swear by an oath, I declined.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:07.92,0:47:14.48,Default,,0,0,0,,It turns out when you swear by an oath, that is binding through numerous lifetimes.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:15.23,0:47:18.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, that's a fact.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:20.34,0:47:22.53,Default,,0,0,0,,It's binding through numerous lifetimes.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:25.61,0:47:34.26,Default,,0,0,0,,So a contract that you swore to several lifetimes ago was binding in this lifetime.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:34.42,0:47:37.69,Default,,0,0,0,,It says, or may the opposite be my fate, and it was.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:38.05,0:47:44.59,Default,,0,0,0,,So the missing thumb was the consequence of a karmic bondage
Dialogue: 0,0:47:44.59,0:47:48.73,Default,,0,0,0,,that I swore to in a previous lifetime, yeah?
Dialogue: 0,0:47:50.88,0:47:52.44,Default,,0,0,0,,The karma came forth in this lifetime.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:52.46,0:47:57.65,Default,,0,0,0,,In the circular saw, I'd do circular saws for years, no problem.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:57.82,0:47:59.11,Default,,0,0,0,,All of a sudden, of its own.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:02.50,0:48:07.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, that was the karmic debt.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:08.23,0:48:08.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Resist.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:09.36,0:48:10.88,Default,,0,0,0,,And it is now paid off.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:11.13,0:48:11.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Resist.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:17.19,0:48:19.61,Default,,0,0,0,,I have but two thumbs to give to my country, you know what I'm saying?
Dialogue: 0,0:48:22.34,0:48:26.32,Default,,0,0,0,,So therefore, I recommend swearing no oaths.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:26.32,0:48:28.90,Default,,0,0,0,,And it says somewhere in Christian literature,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:29.13,0:48:30.48,Default,,0,0,0,,I think that is also teaching,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:30.59,0:48:34.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Christianity, to swear no oaths, swear no oaths, et cetera.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:35.67,0:48:38.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Because they're binding, you don't remember it in this lifetime,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:38.94,0:48:41.76,Default,,0,0,0,,and suddenly it's payola time, yeah?
Dialogue: 0,0:48:43.34,0:48:44.34,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:45.88,0:48:48.84,Default,,0,0,0,,True spiritual integrity, that means you are completely free.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:49.34,0:48:51.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Free to come and go as you want.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:51.26,0:48:52.36,Default,,0,0,0,,There's nothing God has signed.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:52.46,0:48:53.42,Default,,0,0,0,,There's no consequences.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:53.61,0:48:54.42,Default,,0,0,0,,There's no dues.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:55.36,0:48:57.21,Default,,0,0,0,,There's a commonality of purpose.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:58.03,0:49:00.50,Default,,0,0,0,,The commonality is what brings us together.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:00.50,0:49:00.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:01.75,0:49:05.19,Default,,0,0,0,,The only thing that brings us together is that we're all interested in spiritual evolution
Dialogue: 0,0:49:05.19,0:49:06.15,Default,,0,0,0,,for its own sake.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:06.96,0:49:09.53,Default,,0,0,0,,And out of worship, out of love for God,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:09.82,0:49:13.17,Default,,0,0,0,,is a glory and excelsis Deo.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:13.78,0:49:16.23,Default,,0,0,0,,All glory be to Thee, O Lord, Most High.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:16.44,0:49:17.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Out of worship and love,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:18.92,0:49:25.63,Default,,0,0,0,,and by the acknowledgement that God is our source,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:26.38,0:49:28.28,Default,,0,0,0,,and that we are answerable to God,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:28.28,0:49:32.44,Default,,0,0,0,,and by that is our salvation,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:32.65,0:49:34.46,Default,,0,0,0,,our own souls are saved, you see?
Dialogue: 0,0:49:35.26,0:49:39.69,Default,,0,0,0,,We achieve salvation via the acknowledgement of divinity.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:40.63,0:49:43.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, the strange thing about the calibration system that we use
Dialogue: 0,0:49:43.86,0:49:46.28,Default,,0,0,0,,is it cannot be used by atheists.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:46.80,0:49:46.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:47.48,0:49:52.00,Default,,0,0,0,,And I didn't discover that until relatively a few years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:52.51,0:49:55.50,Default,,0,0,0,,But there were people who were using the technique
Dialogue: 0,0:49:55.50,0:49:57.28,Default,,0,0,0,,and would report negative results,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:57.32,0:50:00.76,Default,,0,0,0,,and I thought, you know, this guy's into alternate medicine.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:00.76,0:50:03.48,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, he should assume he's probably been used,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:03.51,0:50:04.25,Default,,0,0,0,,he's been using this for years,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:04.32,0:50:07.25,Default,,0,0,0,,and you find out that he doesn't know,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:07.44,0:50:08.76,Default,,0,0,0,,he doesn't get the right answer.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:09.80,0:50:12.76,Default,,0,0,0,,And then I found out the reason he is negative
Dialogue: 0,0:50:12.76,0:50:14.19,Default,,0,0,0,,is because he's an atheist.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:14.57,0:50:17.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, well, the fact that he's a professor with a fancy beard and all,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:18.25,0:50:19.38,Default,,0,0,0,,you figure, you forgot.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:19.63,0:50:22.40,Default,,0,0,0,,The reason he can't get truth out of something
Dialogue: 0,0:50:22.40,0:50:25.11,Default,,0,0,0,,that we get truth out of all day around the clock
Dialogue: 0,0:50:25.11,0:50:27.59,Default,,0,0,0,,is because he's an atheist.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:27.86,0:50:28.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:28.88,0:50:32.63,Default,,0,0,0,,So the technique that we use cannot be used by atheists.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:32.63,0:50:33.67,Default,,0,0,0,,If you deny,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:33.82,0:50:38.36,Default,,0,0,0,,the very source and backbone and structure of truth itself,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:38.78,0:50:41.38,Default,,0,0,0,,then you're denied the fruits of truth, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:41.98,0:50:45.25,Default,,0,0,0,,So if you deny truth or divinity as the source of truth,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:45.82,0:50:46.90,Default,,0,0,0,,then you cannot use,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:47.11,0:50:48.82,Default,,0,0,0,,you wouldn't get the same answers we get.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:49.36,0:50:51.07,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know if you get any answers at all,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:51.13,0:50:52.07,Default,,0,0,0,,and you might get the opposite.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:53.65,0:50:55.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway, that explains it.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:57.80,0:50:58.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:59.03,0:51:02.21,Default,,0,0,0,,If you refute divinity,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:02.21,0:51:06.03,Default,,0,0,0,,then you cannot find the answers,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:06.38,0:51:08.82,Default,,0,0,0,,to questions such as we do routinely.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:09.71,0:51:13.55,Default,,0,0,0,,And we don't ask, you know, just profound questions all the time.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:14.13,0:51:17.44,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll just say, you know, I really should take that Cipro.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:19.23,0:51:21.82,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll say, I think I'm getting the flu.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:21.94,0:51:22.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, no, yes, yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:22.96,0:51:24.32,Default,,0,0,0,,I should take Cipro, yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:24.34,0:51:26.01,Default,,0,0,0,,I should take two a day, yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:26.11,0:51:27.23,Default,,0,0,0,,I should take three a day, no.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:27.55,0:51:28.69,Default,,0,0,0,,I should take it for how long?
Dialogue: 0,0:51:28.73,0:51:29.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Eight days, nine days, ten days.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:30.15,0:51:32.01,Default,,0,0,0,,So we prescribe medicine for ourselves,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:32.23,0:51:33.80,Default,,0,0,0,,treat ourselves, have all kinds of things.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:34.42,0:51:35.25,Default,,0,0,0,,You know what I mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:51:35.71,0:51:36.44,Default,,0,0,0,,You say, what's the best?
Dialogue: 0,0:51:36.55,0:51:37.30,Default,,0,0,0,,I'd die for the dog.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:37.44,0:51:40.82,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, we use this routinely as part of our life.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:41.57,0:51:43.86,Default,,0,0,0,,And it just really makes life so much easier.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:44.50,0:51:45.82,Default,,0,0,0,,It makes life so much easier.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:46.86,0:51:50.13,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, we shouldn't take the traffic on so-and-so parkway.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:50.28,0:51:51.46,Default,,0,0,0,,It's just going to be impossible.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:51.67,0:51:54.21,Default,,0,0,0,,We get, yes, it's better to take the other parkway.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:54.30,0:51:55.40,Default,,0,0,0,,So, I mean, we use it for, you know,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:55.42,0:51:58.30,Default,,0,0,0,,it doesn't have to be profound stuff like the will of God or something.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:58.86,0:52:02.90,Default,,0,0,0,,It'd just be, I'd be more comfortable with these pants on than the corduroy.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:03.07,0:52:04.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, in Long Beach, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:04.80,0:52:06.50,Default,,0,0,0,,I put these on, you'd be more comfortable.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:06.73,0:52:07.96,Default,,0,0,0,,And corduroy, it'll be too warm.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:08.03,0:52:09.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, okay, you know what I mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:52:17.17,0:52:19.57,Default,,0,0,0,,I just wanted to see the practicality.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:19.67,0:52:21.75,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a very domestic thing to do.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:22.38,0:52:25.61,Default,,0,0,0,,I want to take it out of the idea of being charming or, you know,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:26.19,0:52:28.38,Default,,0,0,0,,anything exceptional or esoteric.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:29.09,0:52:30.34,Default,,0,0,0,,It's very domestic.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:31.15,0:52:33.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Calibrating the laws of consciousness is very domestic,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:33.63,0:52:37.71,Default,,0,0,0,,very practical, very down-to-earth, you know what I'm saying?
Dialogue: 0,0:52:37.71,0:52:41.48,Default,,0,0,0,,And you just make it part of your lifestyle.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:42.26,0:52:48.90,Default,,0,0,0,,And I'll say, that canned dog food is what's giving the dog diarrhea resistance.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:49.46,0:52:50.40,Default,,0,0,0,,I got the answer there.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:50.51,0:52:51.57,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't have to go and pay a bet.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:55.98,0:52:56.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Right.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:56.84,0:52:57.78,Default,,0,0,0,,She was eating grass.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:57.86,0:52:58.61,Default,,0,0,0,,That's what did it.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:59.38,0:52:59.59,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:59.73,0:53:05.86,Default,,0,0,0,,So, you make it, you make spiritual reality fulfilling.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:06.05,0:53:07.53,Default,,0,0,0,,You make it part of your life.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:07.53,0:53:16.65,Default,,0,0,0,,It's benign, and it becomes a blessing in your life.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:16.78,0:53:22.80,Default,,0,0,0,,So, the way we use it, the way I try to teach it is practical, domestic use.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:23.51,0:53:25.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Take away any ooh or ah.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:25.26,0:53:26.80,Default,,0,0,0,,There's nothing mystical or magical.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:27.15,0:53:28.38,Default,,0,0,0,,There's nothing esoteric.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:29.78,0:53:34.03,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't have to go and take courses on how to do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:34.46,0:53:35.67,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a very simple thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:36.55,0:53:37.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Truth, because it matches.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:37.90,0:53:42.09,Default,,0,0,0,,You see, the infinite potentiality, when it's matched with the reality,
Dialogue: 0,0:53:42.09,0:53:48.96,Default,,0,0,0,,by virtue of quantum mechanics, when I say, this is, and it already has a reality,
Dialogue: 0,0:53:49.59,0:53:50.50,Default,,0,0,0,,her arm goes strong.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:51.32,0:53:55.38,Default,,0,0,0,,If I say, this is, and this is not, there's no reality, and the arm goes weak.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:56.13,0:53:57.57,Default,,0,0,0,,It's impersonal.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:57.86,0:54:02.34,Default,,0,0,0,,So, what you're doing is matching potentiality with actuality
Dialogue: 0,0:54:02.34,0:54:06.55,Default,,0,0,0,,in the quantum dimension of the infinite field of consciousness.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:07.76,0:54:10.07,Default,,0,0,0,,What gives her arm strength is the truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:10.07,0:54:12.28,Default,,0,0,0,,If I say, if I'm holding in mind, it's over.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:12.32,0:54:14.94,Default,,0,0,0,,It's over 200, and that's true, then her arm goes strong.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:15.67,0:54:17.32,Default,,0,0,0,,So, truth makes you go strong.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:17.57,0:54:18.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Falsehood makes you go weak.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:19.55,0:54:20.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Goodness makes you go strong.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:21.42,0:54:22.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Wickedness makes you go weak.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:22.92,0:54:24.00,Default,,0,0,0,,It's very, very simple.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:24.63,0:54:27.15,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't have to go to college just to learn that, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:28.26,0:54:31.82,Default,,0,0,0,,What? What did you say?
Dialogue: 0,0:54:31.82,0:54:32.67,Default,,0,0,0,,It's 1230.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:33.46,0:54:34.71,Default,,0,0,0,,She said it's 1230.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:36.90,0:54:38.67,Default,,0,0,0,,She's making threats behind my back.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:46.55,0:54:49.78,Default,,0,0,0,,She said, we love you all, and therefore, we have to let you go and have lunch.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:50.55,0:54:52.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Otherwise, you'll keel over it later.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:00.86,0:55:01.80,Default,,0,0,0,,So, where are we?
Dialogue: 0,0:55:04.34,0:55:07.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, we're talking about
Dialogue: 0,0:55:07.28,0:55:12.26,Default,,0,0,0,,integrous spiritual teachers and teachings.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:13.92,0:55:22.88,Default,,0,0,0,,And non-binding, it means freedom to participate, to come and to go.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:23.57,0:55:27.88,Default,,0,0,0,,It means to inspire people in the direction that you know of spiritual evolution.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:30.01,0:55:34.86,Default,,0,0,0,,And non-involvement in world affairs.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:35.51,0:55:36.86,Default,,0,0,0,,In other words, we're not signing.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:36.94,0:55:40.05,Default,,0,0,0,,We're not signed up with anything that it should win and somebody else should lose.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:41.11,0:55:47.25,Default,,0,0,0,,The intention is benign and non-dualistic.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:48.63,0:55:56.55,Default,,0,0,0,,All transpires by virtue of karmic propensity within the field by which potentiality manifests as actuality,
Dialogue: 0,0:55:56.86,0:55:58.86,Default,,0,0,0,,rather than cause and effect.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:59.01,0:56:00.28,Default,,0,0,0,,So, that's where we ended up.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:00.40,0:56:06.57,Default,,0,0,0,,We were talking about things occur as a consequence, not of a volitional in a Newtonian paradigm,
Dialogue: 0,0:56:06.57,0:56:08.26,Default,,0,0,0,,but as a consequence.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:08.26,0:56:16.86,Default,,0,0,0,,A consequence of emergence, potentiality becoming actuality, which is activated by intention.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:17.23,0:56:24.30,Default,,0,0,0,,So, spiritual intention, then, by itself, actualizes your own spiritual potential.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:25.34,0:56:32.34,Default,,0,0,0,,The minute you acknowledge the divinity of God as the author of all existence,
Dialogue: 0,0:56:32.80,0:56:37.92,Default,,0,0,0,,you've already brought into play a very powerful energy field.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:38.32,0:56:39.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's look at the divinity of God.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:39.40,0:56:58.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's say, that which we do in each of these, yes, calibrates over 600, 800, 750, 800.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:58.86,0:56:59.09,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:59.21,0:57:03.38,Default,,0,0,0,,So, the opening invocation calibrates to 750.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:03.57,0:57:05.82,Default,,0,0,0,,That sets the intention of the lecture.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:07.32,0:57:09.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Glory be to thee, O Lord, Most High.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:09.51,0:57:13.13,Default,,0,0,0,,The Lord of the Universe, God, acknowledges divinity as the source of all existence.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:14.34,0:57:17.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Merely acknowledging that God is the source of all existence,
Dialogue: 0,0:57:18.82,0:57:22.11,Default,,0,0,0,,and that what is answerable, therefore, to divinity,
Dialogue: 0,0:57:23.01,0:57:25.05,Default,,0,0,0,,every hair on your head shall be counted.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:25.42,0:57:25.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's see.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:26.69,0:57:29.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Every hair on your head shall be counted.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:29.86,0:57:30.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Is it a fact?
Dialogue: 0,0:57:30.78,0:57:31.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Resist.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:32.23,0:57:33.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Calibrates at 1,000.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:35.34,0:57:36.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Calibrates at 1,000.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:38.01,0:57:39.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Calibrates at 900.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:39.84,0:57:40.61,Default,,0,0,0,,950.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:42.23,0:57:42.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:42.63,0:57:43.50,Default,,0,0,0,,That's good enough.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:43.63,0:57:44.00,Default,,0,0,0,,900.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:45.92,0:57:55.11,Default,,0,0,0,,The last 50 is God's grace, despite all the hairs on your head.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:55.90,0:57:57.98,Default,,0,0,0,,That may not vote in your favor.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:00.11,0:58:06.17,Default,,0,0,0,,The last 50 points is the generosity of the grace of God.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:06.34,0:58:06.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Resist.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:07.28,0:58:07.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Aha.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:09.34,0:58:13.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Even though you don't acknowledge it yourself and own it and realize it,
Dialogue: 0,0:58:14.55,0:58:19.32,Default,,0,0,0,,God's grace releases you from that.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:19.65,0:58:21.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Because he sees your limitation.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:22.59,0:58:22.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh-huh.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:23.94,0:58:24.51,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:24.55,0:58:26.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, that certainly is heartening.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:27.19,0:58:28.78,Default,,0,0,0,,That takes care of the fear of death.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:28.88,0:58:30.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Anybody still have a fear of death here?
Dialogue: 0,0:58:32.86,0:58:35.26,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm going to kill anybody that's still afraid of death.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:39.92,0:58:42.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Anybody that's had a near-death experience,
Dialogue: 0,0:58:43.59,0:58:46.59,Default,,0,0,0,,it's laughable that one should be afraid of death, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:47.48,0:58:50.94,Default,,0,0,0,,In fact, it's quite the opposite of the consequence.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:51.59,0:58:54.61,Default,,0,0,0,,You think you're leaving, and then when you realize you're not,
Dialogue: 0,0:58:55.26,0:58:57.94,Default,,0,0,0,,that's when the pain comes in.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:59.51,0:59:01.21,Default,,0,0,0,,You're going back to where you were.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:02.19,0:59:03.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, God.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:03.28,0:59:04.40,Default,,0,0,0,,I thought I was leaving.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:04.61,0:59:05.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, well.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:05.63,0:59:05.84,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:07.48,0:59:11.80,Default,,0,0,0,,I've been almost left a number of times.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:11.80,0:59:15.42,Default,,0,0,0,,And I always remember there's a feeling of disappointment.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:16.38,0:59:19.32,Default,,0,0,0,,You're all ready to leave, and you're in this beatific state,
Dialogue: 0,0:59:19.65,0:59:20.90,Default,,0,0,0,,and then you get the bad news.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:23.21,0:59:25.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Unfortunately, you're not dying.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:25.51,0:59:25.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:26.48,0:59:27.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, well.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:31.23,0:59:36.23,Default,,0,0,0,,So, well, we tried to cover all the important slides.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:36.32,0:59:39.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, we still have some more to do before we get to the question and answer period.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:40.00,0:59:40.98,Default,,0,0,0,,So, let's see.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:41.05,0:59:42.01,Default,,0,0,0,,What's the next one?
Dialogue: 0,0:59:44.46,0:59:44.76,Default,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:59:49.03,0:59:51.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, we were talking about spiritual integrity,
Dialogue: 0,0:59:52.05,0:59:55.07,Default,,0,0,0,,equality of all the students and the teachers,
Dialogue: 0,0:59:56.17,0:59:57.94,Default,,0,0,0,,beyond proof.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:59.38,1:00:01.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Divinity is not provable.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:01.05,1:00:01.88,Default,,0,0,0,,It's demonic.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:02.09,1:00:02.88,Default,,0,0,0,,It's inconstrable.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:03.09,1:00:03.98,Default,,0,0,0,,We confirm it here.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:04.19,1:00:11.34,Default,,0,0,0,,We confirm it by our own unique techniques, but it's not provable.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:11.55,1:00:13.98,Default,,0,0,0,,So, spiritual reality, because it deals with context,
Dialogue: 0,1:00:14.19,1:00:16.63,Default,,0,0,0,,the only thing that's provable is content.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:16.82,1:00:21.51,Default,,0,0,0,,So, anything that you can actually prove is not the ultimate truth to begin with.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:21.71,1:00:28.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Anything you can prove within the linear Newtonian paradigm, it's limited.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:28.26,1:00:31.96,Default,,0,0,0,,That which is unlimited context, unlimited context,
Dialogue: 0,1:00:32.05,1:00:32.88,Default,,0,0,0,,cannot be proven.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:33.46,1:00:34.36,Default,,0,0,0,,It just is.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:36.44,1:00:42.90,Default,,0,0,0,,And then what happens is you begin to, there's the realization
Dialogue: 0,1:00:42.90,1:00:45.61,Default,,0,0,0,,that one is not the linear content of consciousness,
Dialogue: 0,1:00:46.48,1:00:50.86,Default,,0,0,0,,that one is consciousness itself, that which is aware.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:52.80,1:00:57.36,Default,,0,0,0,,So, awareness, awareness itself is then the function.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:57.63,1:00:59.90,Default,,0,0,0,,So, when people say, how can I give up the ego,
Dialogue: 0,1:01:00.59,1:01:03.38,Default,,0,0,0,,which we may talk about a little bit later if we have time,
Dialogue: 0,1:01:03.71,1:01:06.28,Default,,0,0,0,,how can we give up the ego?
Dialogue: 0,1:01:06.46,1:01:10.73,Default,,0,0,0,,You give up yourself as primary cause.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:10.94,1:01:15.98,Default,,0,0,0,,You give up the illusion that you, your personal self,
Dialogue: 0,1:01:16.17,1:01:20.23,Default,,0,0,0,,is what's deciding and making the decisions.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:20.44,1:01:23.40,Default,,0,0,0,,A more advanced understanding, you begin to see
Dialogue: 0,1:01:23.59,1:01:26.75,Default,,0,0,0,,that everything is happening spontaneously,
Dialogue: 0,1:01:26.94,1:01:34.36,Default,,0,0,0,,and the illusion that there's a personal self causing it is itself an illusion.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:34.55,1:01:37.23,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a spontaneous illusion, so you don't have
Dialogue: 0,1:01:37.23,1:01:39.55,Default,,0,0,0,,to feel guilty that you have an ego.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:39.76,1:01:43.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Everybody has an ego or we wouldn't be here, would we?
Dialogue: 0,1:01:43.69,1:01:46.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Without the ego, you wouldn't stay alive long enough.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:46.96,1:01:50.36,Default,,0,0,0,,So, the ego serves a purpose and it keeps our animal,
Dialogue: 0,1:01:50.57,1:01:53.48,Default,,0,0,0,,keeps our animal going, keeps our animal alive.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:53.69,1:01:57.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Tells you to stay out of the way of the lions and things like this.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:57.80,1:02:01.11,Default,,0,0,0,,So, we owe our physical survival to the ego,
Dialogue: 0,1:02:01.32,1:02:02.88,Default,,0,0,0,,but then it becomes a limitation.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:03.07,1:02:07.32,Default,,0,0,0,,So, at a certain level of consciousness, that which served us well,
Dialogue: 0,1:02:07.69,1:02:11.21,Default,,0,0,0,,at the lower levels, now becomes the barrier.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:11.42,1:02:14.90,Default,,0,0,0,,How to transcend the illusion of a personal self.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:15.11,1:02:20.75,Default,,0,0,0,,The idea of a personal self occurs spontaneously.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:20.94,1:02:23.11,Default,,0,0,0,,So, we don't have to feel guilty that we have it.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:23.30,1:02:26.46,Default,,0,0,0,,It's normal.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:26.65,1:02:28.17,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a natural consequence.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:28.38,1:02:31.82,Default,,0,0,0,,We see phenomena happen and we presume
Dialogue: 0,1:02:32.01,1:02:35.09,Default,,0,0,0,,that there's a personal self that makes it happen.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:35.30,1:02:39.82,Default,,0,0,0,,We presume that a personal self weighs this arm.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:40.50,1:02:42.50,Default,,0,0,0,,If we're fast enough, if we're fast enough,
Dialogue: 0,1:02:42.69,1:02:47.67,Default,,0,0,0,,and this is all a matter of speed, you will catch that that happened
Dialogue: 0,1:02:47.86,1:02:51.42,Default,,0,0,0,,just prior to your taking credit for it.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:51.61,1:02:55.42,Default,,0,0,0,,You say, I decided to move the arm up there,
Dialogue: 0,1:02:55.61,1:02:59.78,Default,,0,0,0,,but you're one ten thousandth of a second behind the eight ball.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:59.98,1:03:04.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's see, that is one ten thousandth of a second resistant.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:05.01,1:03:11.94,Default,,0,0,0,,So, the leading edge of the ego then is one ten thousandth of a second ahead
Dialogue: 0,1:03:11.94,1:03:19.01,Default,,0,0,0,,of reality, and you reach a point of consciousness where you can transcend
Dialogue: 0,1:03:19.21,1:03:22.78,Default,,0,0,0,,that one tenth of one ten thousandth of a second.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:22.98,1:03:28.07,Default,,0,0,0,,And you catch that the ego is taking credit for what has already happened.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:28.26,1:03:30.75,Default,,0,0,0,,And I think I've told you in previous lectures,
Dialogue: 0,1:03:30.94,1:03:35.09,Default,,0,0,0,,I discovered that when I was still an adolescent or
Dialogue: 0,1:03:35.30,1:03:36.01,Default,,0,0,0,,no, no, no.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:36.21,1:03:38.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, probably an adolescent, 18 or 19.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:38.82,1:03:41.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway, a rabbit, I was driving the car.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:41.61,1:03:42.90,Default,,0,0,0,,You won't want to lay for it.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:43.09,1:03:48.38,Default,,0,0,0,,And and a rabbit ran across the road instantly.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:48.57,1:03:52.38,Default,,0,0,0,,The foot went down on the brake and saved the rabbit.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:52.57,1:03:55.09,Default,,0,0,0,,And I caught the ego claiming credit for that.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:55.30,1:04:00.34,Default,,0,0,0,,I caught the ego saying I put my foot on the brake.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:00.53,1:04:06.98,Default,,0,0,0,,The foot was already on the brake when the eye jumped in and credit for that.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:07.17,1:04:12.05,Default,,0,0,0,,So I caught I caught the ego at it at a very young age before I knew anything
Dialogue: 0,1:04:12.26,1:04:14.53,Default,,0,0,0,,about consciousness or anything like that.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:14.78,1:04:19.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Ego jumped in and instantly claimed credit for saving the rabbit's life.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:19.73,1:04:25.17,Default,,0,0,0,,No, it happened before before the eye made a decision.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:25.38,1:04:28.57,Default,,0,0,0,,The instant breaking happened instantly.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:28.76,1:04:31.98,Default,,0,0,0,,And then the eye complimented itself,
Dialogue: 0,1:04:32.19,1:04:36.26,Default,,0,0,0,,which is egotism, which we'll talk about later.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:36.46,1:04:38.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Susan and I, if we have time for it,
Dialogue: 0,1:04:38.46,1:04:42.46,Default,,0,0,0,,we want to just finish the review of these particular lectures.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:42.65,1:04:43.73,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:43.94,1:04:45.26,Default,,0,0,0,,So
Dialogue: 0,1:04:45.73,1:04:50.40,Default,,0,0,0,,mystical is a word that we will talk.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:50.61,1:04:53.23,Default,,0,0,0,,There's a few slides on mysticism later.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:53.42,1:04:58.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Mysticism is that emergence as the ego collapses.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:58.78,1:05:02.67,Default,,0,0,0,,The mysticism then is an inner knowingness.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:02.86,1:05:10.13,Default,,0,0,0,,It's the inner awareness of the non-linear as the linear as you're less
Dialogue: 0,1:05:10.32,1:05:16.05,Default,,0,0,0,,less and less dominated by the egotism of the linear domain and thinking this.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:16.05,1:05:19.32,Default,,0,0,0,,And you give up thinking this is a bad habit.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:19.51,1:05:24.17,Default,,0,0,0,,And you let go of thinking this awareness takes over instead.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:24.38,1:05:28.96,Default,,0,0,0,,This can be achieved through meditation and contemplation as well.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:29.15,1:05:33.11,Default,,0,0,0,,You can adopt a contemplative
Dialogue: 0,1:05:33.30,1:05:39.26,Default,,0,0,0,,style and way of being aware within the world so that you're not
Dialogue: 0,1:05:39.46,1:05:42.65,Default,,0,0,0,,not thinking in a linear dimension at all.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:42.86,1:05:45.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Instead, you're sort of automatically
Dialogue: 0,1:05:45.09,1:05:48.86,Default,,0,0,0,,adjusting to the overall field in an appropriate way.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:49.05,1:05:50.94,Default,,0,0,0,,And if you're honest with yourself,
Dialogue: 0,1:05:51.13,1:05:54.98,Default,,0,0,0,,you'll see that this is happening of its own.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:55.17,1:05:58.09,Default,,0,0,0,,The awareness of consciousness itself is
Dialogue: 0,1:05:58.30,1:06:03.69,Default,,0,0,0,,such that you automatically get out of the way of the trolley car
Dialogue: 0,1:06:03.90,1:06:07.94,Default,,0,0,0,,because that's the sense of reality that comes out of the infinite field.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:08.13,1:06:09.82,Default,,0,0,0,,So the field knows that you shouldn't
Dialogue: 0,1:06:10.01,1:06:13.42,Default,,0,0,0,,be standing on the trolley car tracks and it moves you off.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:13.61,1:06:15.46,Default,,0,0,0,,And it isn't that the ego.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:15.65,1:06:18.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Decided, man, it's dangerous standing here.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:18.42,1:06:23.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Nobody says to themselves, I think it's dangerous to stand here on the trolley tracks.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:23.30,1:06:24.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Remember saying that to yourself?
Dialogue: 0,1:06:24.94,1:06:28.03,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't think I should be standing on these trolley tracks.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:28.23,1:06:30.38,Default,,0,0,0,,I think I will get off before the cable car gets here.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:30.59,1:06:33.30,Default,,0,0,0,,No, you do it automatically.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:33.50,1:06:39.57,Default,,0,0,0,,So that which we often disregard because we say it's just automatic is
Dialogue: 0,1:06:39.78,1:06:45.98,Default,,0,0,0,,is the effect of perception, it's the effect of the knowingness of the
Dialogue: 0,1:06:46.17,1:06:53.15,Default,,0,0,0,,infinite field of consciousness itself as we let go of the illusion that we're
Dialogue: 0,1:06:53.34,1:06:57.78,Default,,0,0,0,,being dominated by logic and cause and effect and the linear domain.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:57.98,1:07:00.11,Default,,0,0,0,,We begin to see that we've been taking
Dialogue: 0,1:07:00.30,1:07:06.51,Default,,0,0,0,,credit, that actually everything is happening autonomously by itself.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:06.71,1:07:12.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Only once in a while does the mind come in in any kind of a meaningful way.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:13.19,1:07:15.75,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, shall I have a ham sandwich or a cheese sandwich?
Dialogue: 0,1:07:15.94,1:07:18.63,Default,,0,0,0,,That was the ego's big moment today.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:18.82,1:07:24.96,Default,,0,0,0,,The fact that you are that you're there, that you're eating all this has been
Dialogue: 0,1:07:25.15,1:07:29.28,Default,,0,0,0,,decided for you, the fact that you need to work to make a living and pay the bills.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:29.48,1:07:32.71,Default,,0,0,0,,All this all this phenomena is outside your saying this.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:32.92,1:07:34.88,Default,,0,0,0,,So what you're allowed to choose today is
Dialogue: 0,1:07:35.07,1:07:37.36,Default,,0,0,0,,whether you want a cheese sandwich or a ham sandwich.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:37.55,1:07:43.17,Default,,0,0,0,,And that's the limit of your freedom.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:43.38,1:07:48.46,Default,,0,0,0,,The idea of free choice is free choice is one of the great illusions of the world.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:48.65,1:07:52.57,Default,,0,0,0,,And people give up all kinds of stuff for what they call freedom of speech, etc.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:52.78,1:07:56.53,Default,,0,0,0,,And and anyway, they quickly bring freedom.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:56.53,1:07:58.40,Default,,0,0,0,,The way to eliminate freedom of speech is
Dialogue: 0,1:07:58.40,1:08:03.01,Default,,0,0,0,,to give people real freedom of speech and they will quickly get rid of free speech.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:05.21,1:08:06.00,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:06.19,1:08:10.23,Default,,0,0,0,,So the origination of truth is a spontaneous knowingness.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:10.44,1:08:11.84,Default,,0,0,0,,It's like a radiance.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:12.03,1:08:13.84,Default,,0,0,0,,It's like an illumination.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:14.05,1:08:22.80,Default,,0,0,0,,And therefore, there is no personal self, no cause effect, no verbs, no me.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:23.00,1:08:24.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Causing of that. All right.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:24.76,1:08:28.42,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll go to the next because we want to finish all these slides.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:28.61,1:08:30.22,Default,,0,0,0,,OK.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:32.64,1:08:34.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Truth is always affirmative.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:34.72,1:08:40.23,Default,,0,0,0,,It doesn't say not this, not that it says this instead of that.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:40.43,1:08:41.94,Default,,0,0,0,,It's invitational.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:42.14,1:08:43.63,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not sentimental.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:43.82,1:08:46.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Emotionality is based on perception.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:46.75,1:08:50.55,Default,,0,0,0,,So a lot of truth gets lost in the emotionality.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:50.75,1:08:53.14,Default,,0,0,0,,This happens to me in politics very much.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:53.35,1:08:54.98,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, something gets to be
Dialogue: 0,1:08:55.22,1:08:58.18,Default,,0,0,0,,in the popular belief system, the next thing you know, there's a bandwagon.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:58.39,1:08:59.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Everybody's getting on there.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:59.43,1:09:03.02,Default,,0,0,0,,They're waving flags, you know, an earthwarming
Dialogue: 0,1:09:03.22,1:09:06.39,Default,,0,0,0,,rally or something like this, except the earth doesn't pay attention
Dialogue: 0,1:09:06.59,1:09:08.86,Default,,0,0,0,,to the earthwarming rally anyway.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:09.06,1:09:14.43,Default,,0,0,0,,So the people get very emotionally committed to causes and
Dialogue: 0,1:09:14.63,1:09:20.02,Default,,0,0,0,,the narcissistic core of the ego loves to ride the bandwagon on causes.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:20.22,1:09:23.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Whatever is a current popular cause,
Dialogue: 0,1:09:23.43,1:09:25.18,Default,,0,0,0,,uh, how to get rid of your garbage
Dialogue: 0,1:09:25.39,1:09:30.71,Default,,0,0,0,,or whatever it is, people sign up by the drove and become very emotional about it.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:30.90,1:09:34.60,Default,,0,0,0,,So you say, why do they have to become emotional about it?
Dialogue: 0,1:09:34.80,1:09:38.19,Default,,0,0,0,,It's because the core of the ego is narcissistic.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:38.39,1:09:43.35,Default,,0,0,0,,It has to do with me, me, my cause, my belief system
Dialogue: 0,1:09:43.56,1:09:45.76,Default,,0,0,0,,is now becomes very important.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:45.96,1:09:48.15,Default,,0,0,0,,So by exaggerating the importance
Dialogue: 0,1:09:48.35,1:09:54.73,Default,,0,0,0,,of a belief system, all you're doing is increasing the magnitude of the egotism.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:55.93,1:10:00.81,Default,,0,0,0,,And how important your views are on things as you get more sophisticated,
Dialogue: 0,1:10:01.02,1:10:07.50,Default,,0,0,0,,you lose interest in what people's opinions are because they're all stupid.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:12.26,1:10:15.34,Default,,0,0,0,,And for amusement, you can click on to the what do you call it?
Dialogue: 0,1:10:15.53,1:10:17.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Internet system,
Dialogue: 0,1:10:17.65,1:10:21.97,Default,,0,0,0,,getting what they call that system anyway, blogger system.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:22.17,1:10:25.28,Default,,0,0,0,,And you can find endless amusement there
Dialogue: 0,1:10:25.48,1:10:26.09,Default,,0,0,0,,from them.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:26.28,1:10:31.48,Default,,0,0,0,,From the benign to the ridiculous, very ridiculous, you know.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:32.68,1:10:34.48,Default,,0,0,0,,All right. So truth is not sentimental.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:34.68,1:10:37.81,Default,,0,0,0,,It doesn't climb on the bandwagon.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:38.01,1:10:41.78,Default,,0,0,0,,We don't have to save the world through enlightenment.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:43.39,1:10:46.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, I was saved the world through enlightenment rally in Central Park.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:46.78,1:10:52.75,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll bring parades and banners and bugles and and important politicians
Dialogue: 0,1:10:52.94,1:10:56.31,Default,,0,0,0,,and save the world through spiritual advancement.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:56.51,1:10:57.90,Default,,0,0,0,,In consciousness, awareness.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:58.10,1:11:01.94,Default,,0,0,0,,You can imagine how many people will sign up.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:03.39,1:11:07.90,Default,,0,0,0,,People who get what we're really about wouldn't be there, would they?
Dialogue: 0,1:11:12.96,1:11:18.67,Default,,0,0,0,,So it's truth does not do anything or cause anything.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:18.86,1:11:20.31,Default,,0,0,0,,It's non volitional.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:20.51,1:11:22.31,Default,,0,0,0,,It's invitational.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:22.51,1:11:27.30,Default,,0,0,0,,People are either attracted to it and it's meaningful to them or not.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:27.46,1:11:28.85,Default,,0,0,0,,It's non predictive.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:29.06,1:11:32.26,Default,,0,0,0,,It doesn't predict the future.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:32.46,1:11:35.93,Default,,0,0,0,,So the prediction of what's going to happen.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:36.13,1:11:39.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Two thousand and twenty something rather.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:39.78,1:11:41.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Two thousand and twelve.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:41.86,1:11:45.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Get your mortgage paid up by December.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:46.06,1:11:47.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Right before Christmas, right?
Dialogue: 0,1:11:48.14,1:11:50.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, golly, God doesn't even care about Christmas.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:50.82,1:11:53.98,Default,,0,0,0,,He's going to bring the world to an end right before Christmas.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:54.18,1:11:56.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, that's not very kindly, I think.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:56.75,1:11:58.35,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll have to speak to him upstairs.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:58.55,1:12:01.02,Default,,0,0,0,,You could wait till after Christmas.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:01.22,1:12:04.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Have the world in December 26, 2012.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:04.38,1:12:05.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's see.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:08.50,1:12:12.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Why are predictions always fallacious?
Dialogue: 0,1:12:13.11,1:12:17.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Because it's based on an idea of causality.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:17.30,1:12:24.06,Default,,0,0,0,,See, because the world is evolutionary, what's going to be next cannot be decided
Dialogue: 0,1:12:24.27,1:12:31.51,Default,,0,0,0,,now, because what happens is the phenomena of the future are the result
Dialogue: 0,1:12:31.67,1:12:35.14,Default,,0,0,0,,of decisions, decisions made now.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:35.34,1:12:39.02,Default,,0,0,0,,There's no way of knowing what will happen because nobody knows what choices
Dialogue: 0,1:12:39.22,1:12:43.28,Default,,0,0,0,,because of freedom of choice, because of freedom of the will.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:43.48,1:12:50.32,Default,,0,0,0,,It's impossible to predict the future of anything because otherwise there would be
Dialogue: 0,1:12:50.32,1:12:52.77,Default,,0,0,0,,no freedom of the will if there was no freedom of the will.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:52.97,1:12:54.60,Default,,0,0,0,,There would be no answer ability.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:54.81,1:12:57.97,Default,,0,0,0,,There'd be no such thing as karma, et cetera.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:58.17,1:12:59.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Neither would there be liberation.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:59.97,1:13:00.97,Default,,0,0,0,,So
Dialogue: 0,1:13:00.97,1:13:07.78,Default,,0,0,0,,the future cannot be predicted because the future is the consequence of the present
Dialogue: 0,1:13:07.98,1:13:09.75,Default,,0,0,0,,and the present hasn't happened yet.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:09.94,1:13:13.51,Default,,0,0,0,,What will be in the future depends on all the choices that people make.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:13.71,1:13:17.14,Default,,0,0,0,,And those seeing this as of right now, those are unknowable.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:17.35,1:13:22.10,Default,,0,0,0,,There's no way of knowing which way the wind will be blowing on that day because
Dialogue: 0,1:13:22.31,1:13:26.92,Default,,0,0,0,,the factors that contribute to the direction of the wind haven't occurred yet.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:27.11,1:13:27.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Is that obvious?
Dialogue: 0,1:13:28.11,1:13:31.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Anybody got any problem about that?
Dialogue: 0,1:13:31.92,1:13:34.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Nobody. Oh, well.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:34.52,1:13:34.92,Default,,0,0,0,,It must be.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:35.11,1:13:39.00,Default,,0,0,0,,That was that old joke about the kid in the back said the world's going to end
Dialogue: 0,1:13:39.19,1:13:44.92,Default,,0,0,0,,in in 20, 20 billion years, the guy who puts his hand up 20 billion years.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:45.11,1:13:46.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. Oh, my God.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:46.92,1:13:49.18,Default,,0,0,0,,I thought you said 20 million.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:53.47,1:13:58.43,Default,,0,0,0,,So the reason I can safely predict that
Dialogue: 0,1:13:58.63,1:14:02.14,Default,,0,0,0,,the world is not coming to an end in the year 2012,
Dialogue: 0,1:14:02.35,1:14:06.39,Default,,0,0,0,,because if it is, nobody would be around to tell me I'm wrong.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:06.94,1:14:12.22,Default,,0,0,0,,The safest prediction I know.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:12.42,1:14:18.10,Default,,0,0,0,,So I'm betting that the world will still
Dialogue: 0,1:14:18.30,1:14:22.22,Default,,0,0,0,,be here in the year 2012, December 21st or whatever it is.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:22.42,1:14:26.14,Default,,0,0,0,,And besides, God wouldn't be that much of a killjoy and not Christmas out.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:26.34,1:14:27.81,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:28.01,1:14:30.17,Default,,0,0,0,,You wait till December 27th anyway,
Dialogue: 0,1:14:30.36,1:14:33.34,Default,,0,0,0,,after you open your stockings and all that kind of stuff.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:33.53,1:14:36.14,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, that would be mean, wouldn't it?
Dialogue: 0,1:14:36.14,1:14:40.22,Default,,0,0,0,,So it's not predictive and it's not
Dialogue: 0,1:14:40.42,1:14:43.14,Default,,0,0,0,,predictive because of the freedom of the will.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:43.34,1:14:47.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Karmic responsibility is because you have the freedom of choice.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:48.10,1:14:52.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Freedom of choice is what differentiates the consciousness level of humans.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:53.17,1:14:57.97,Default,,0,0,0,,It's because of freedom of choice that you can reach salvation and salvation.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:58.17,1:15:02.56,Default,,0,0,0,,This is the consequence of one's own personal choice.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:02.77,1:15:06.47,Default,,0,0,0,,So God doesn't force anybody to do anything.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:06.68,1:15:09.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Each one of us, by virtue of the choices
Dialogue: 0,1:15:09.27,1:15:12.60,Default,,0,0,0,,and decisions that we make from moment to moment,
Dialogue: 0,1:15:12.80,1:15:16.72,Default,,0,0,0,,decide our own karmic future and propensities.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:16.92,1:15:19.00,Default,,0,0,0,,So I always compare the infinite field
Dialogue: 0,1:15:19.19,1:15:23.72,Default,,0,0,0,,of consciousness to a giant electromagnetic field.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:23.92,1:15:26.47,Default,,0,0,0,,And I compare human beings,
Dialogue: 0,1:15:26.68,1:15:31.23,Default,,0,0,0,,our little spirits to little fragments of metal fragments.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:31.43,1:15:34.19,Default,,0,0,0,,And we have a positive and a negative pole.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:34.39,1:15:36.47,Default,,0,0,0,,So as we make positive
Dialogue: 0,1:15:36.68,1:15:39.27,Default,,0,0,0,,choices, our polarity moves in this direction.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:39.47,1:15:43.50,Default,,0,0,0,,And as we make negative choices, our polarity moves in this direction.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:43.69,1:15:45.65,Default,,0,0,0,,So based on the choices you make,
Dialogue: 0,1:15:45.85,1:15:50.69,Default,,0,0,0,,then like a little iron magnetic filing, your position in the infinite magnetic
Dialogue: 0,1:15:50.89,1:15:54.61,Default,,0,0,0,,field shifts. So if you constantly choose the negative,
Dialogue: 0,1:15:54.81,1:15:59.65,Default,,0,0,0,,you shift down towards this level of the field closer and closer to the hills.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:59.85,1:16:03.97,Default,,0,0,0,,And as you choose on this side, the other polarity comes up.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:04.18,1:16:06.14,Default,,0,0,0,,And because of the infinite power
Dialogue: 0,1:16:06.30,1:16:12.22,Default,,0,0,0,,of the field, so therefore God is not personal and judgmental.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:12.42,1:16:20.27,Default,,0,0,0,,God is the infinite field of power out of which your choices are what decide your fate.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:20.47,1:16:26.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Your choices, you know, your fate is strictly up to your own choices.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:26.52,1:16:29.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Your fate is not up to an arbitrary God,
Dialogue: 0,1:16:29.76,1:16:36.85,Default,,0,0,0,,but strictly within your own hands resist, strictly within your own power resist.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:37.05,1:16:38.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Your karmic destiny
Dialogue: 0,1:16:38.28,1:16:41.56,Default,,0,0,0,,is strictly within your own personal power resist.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:41.76,1:16:43.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Wow.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:43.82,1:16:50.31,Default,,0,0,0,,So there's no point of fearing a God who would act contrary to his own laws.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:50.51,1:16:56.00,Default,,0,0,0,,So the law of divinity is an infinite field of infinite power
Dialogue: 0,1:16:56.19,1:16:59.56,Default,,0,0,0,,within that infinite field of infinite power.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:59.77,1:17:03.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Your choices decide your own fate.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:03.98,1:17:09.71,Default,,0,0,0,,So everyone lives then by the ultimate freedom of his own choices, which by virtue
Dialogue: 0,1:17:09.86,1:17:15.39,Default,,0,0,0,,of the infinite power of the field of divinity determines the outcomes.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:15.59,1:17:22.97,Default,,0,0,0,,We say that God is omniscient, all knowing, omnipotent, all powerful,
Dialogue: 0,1:17:23.18,1:17:29.52,Default,,0,0,0,,all present, all knowing, all powerful because of the nature of the field.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:29.72,1:17:33.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Then our karmic destiny is within our own hand.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:33.85,1:17:37.85,Default,,0,0,0,,There is nobody else steering the canoe except ourself.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:38.05,1:17:42.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore, God needs to be feared, nor hate.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:42.72,1:17:44.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Nor held responsible.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:45.00,1:17:48.47,Default,,0,0,0,,And we alone are responsible for our own destiny.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:48.68,1:17:54.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, we alone are responsible for our own karmic destiny.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:54.69,1:17:58.57,Default,,0,0,0,,And it's by virtue of that that we reach freedom and eventually resist.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:58.77,1:18:02.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Otherwise, if you weren't responsible, you'd never be able to reach freedom either.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:02.34,1:18:03.98,Default,,0,0,0,,So. All right.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:04.18,1:18:06.18,Default,,0,0,0,,So becoming enlightened then is just
Dialogue: 0,1:18:06.39,1:18:13.36,Default,,0,0,0,,progressively seeing all the things that we're talking about until they become automatic.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:13.56,1:18:14.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:14.68,1:18:21.78,Default,,0,0,0,,So we said that one quality of spiritual truth is it's not not predictive
Dialogue: 0,1:18:21.98,1:18:27.47,Default,,0,0,0,,because there's no possible way of knowing the future if the future depends
Dialogue: 0,1:18:27.67,1:18:33.06,Default,,0,0,0,,on the choices that are being made currently by everyone on Earth.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:33.27,1:18:35.02,Default,,0,0,0,,All right. It's not authoritarian.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:35.22,1:18:37.02,Default,,0,0,0,,We let truth speak for itself.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:37.22,1:18:39.39,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not egoistic.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:40.39,1:18:41.59,Default,,0,0,0,,It's educational.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:41.78,1:18:45.06,Default,,0,0,0,,So it's primarily what we do is educational.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:45.71,1:18:49.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Understanding and educational.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:49.93,1:18:53.85,Default,,0,0,0,,It's also devoid of induced altered states of consciousness.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:54.06,1:18:57.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, many people, when they become enamored of the whole spiritual dimension,
Dialogue: 0,1:18:57.65,1:19:04.11,Default,,0,0,0,,are are somewhat, you know, bottled by all the capabilities.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:04.31,1:19:06.47,Default,,0,0,0,,And
Dialogue: 0,1:19:06.68,1:19:08.72,Default,,0,0,0,,there are some towns that are famous for that.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:08.92,1:19:13.96,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, they're called New Age land where everything that's esoteric and sort
Dialogue: 0,1:19:14.15,1:19:16.76,Default,,0,0,0,,of far out has a big following, you see.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:16.96,1:19:20.10,Default,,0,0,0,,And
Dialogue: 0,1:19:20.30,1:19:25.38,Default,,0,0,0,,this is natural because when you find begin to find out there's something
Dialogue: 0,1:19:25.57,1:19:30.77,Default,,0,0,0,,to life other than just the pragmatic every day.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:30.97,1:19:34.10,Default,,0,0,0,,So what's in the ego and logic is there?
Dialogue: 0,1:19:34.30,1:19:40.84,Default,,0,0,0,,And you find that there are other dimensions and then people become enamored of other dimensions.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:41.03,1:19:44.03,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not something I recommend.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:44.23,1:19:48.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Why? Because you can get lost there for a long, long time.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:49.07,1:19:51.96,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, you know, 500 lifetimes.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:52.15,1:19:56.25,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, you can get lost there for a long, long time when you start wandering off
Dialogue: 0,1:19:56.44,1:19:58.21,Default,,0,0,0,,into other dimensions.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:58.40,1:20:03.44,Default,,0,0,0,,So what is esoteric and what is spiritual are two different things.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:03.64,1:20:09.80,Default,,0,0,0,,So without consciousness calibration, you can't really tell without consciousness.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:10.00,1:20:15.22,Default,,0,0,0,,And so therefore, I don't recommend psychics and people from other dimensions,
Dialogue: 0,1:20:15.43,1:20:19.22,Default,,0,0,0,,people from other realms and other dimensions, even if they're even if
Dialogue: 0,1:20:19.43,1:20:23.81,Default,,0,0,0,,one or so is the wrong direction to go.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:24.02,1:20:28.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Why? Because, you know, as it says in the Christian literature,
Dialogue: 0,1:20:29.02,1:20:32.22,Default,,0,0,0,,it's not that the other dimensions don't exist.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:32.42,1:20:34.22,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not that they don't exist.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:34.42,1:20:40.06,Default,,0,0,0,,It's just that they will lead you into the endless dimensions of which there is no return.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:40.26,1:20:43.85,Default,,0,0,0,,So you can keep wandering from one dimension to the next dimension
Dialogue: 0,1:20:44.06,1:20:48.73,Default,,0,0,0,,and stay there for, you know, millennia because there's no return.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:48.73,1:20:51.38,Default,,0,0,0,,So there's an infinite number of other dimensions.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:51.57,1:20:55.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's ask that we have permission to ask that.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:55.72,1:21:00.01,Default,,0,0,0,,There is an infinite number of other dimensions resist.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:00.21,1:21:01.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Wow.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:02.02,1:21:04.26,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm glad we didn't go there for our vacation.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:04.46,1:21:05.85,Default,,0,0,0,,After all,
Dialogue: 0,1:21:10.64,1:21:15.46,Default,,0,0,0,,we were going to go to woo woo woo woo land.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:19.73,1:21:24.05,Default,,0,0,0,,And the town where we come from has many woo woo people.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:24.25,1:21:24.81,Default,,0,0,0,,So it's
Dialogue: 0,1:21:25.01,1:21:25.81,Default,,0,0,0,,woo woo heaven.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:26.01,1:21:31.81,Default,,0,0,0,,And no, the Bible says it doesn't say that they don't exist.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:32.02,1:21:35.18,Default,,0,0,0,,It just says not to go there.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:35.38,1:21:38.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Other other dimensions do exist.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:38.42,1:21:44.14,Default,,0,0,0,,So so the child in you wants to explore them.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:44.34,1:21:48.69,Default,,0,0,0,,And of course, many lifetimes later, you're still out there.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:48.89,1:21:51.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Because how do you find your way back?
Dialogue: 0,1:21:51.22,1:21:56.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Having just, you know, worked your way into another dimension
Dialogue: 0,1:21:56.47,1:21:59.47,Default,,0,0,0,,to get back, you would have to know
Dialogue: 0,1:21:59.67,1:22:03.55,Default,,0,0,0,,how to get back from that dimension to this dimension.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:03.75,1:22:06.06,Default,,0,0,0,,And for some, there is no return.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:06.27,1:22:08.86,Default,,0,0,0,,For some, there is no return.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:09.06,1:22:15.30,Default,,0,0,0,,So it's not exactly something you wish upon yourself to be lost wandering
Dialogue: 0,1:22:15.50,1:22:18.53,Default,,0,0,0,,through eternity, through endless dimensions,
Dialogue: 0,1:22:18.73,1:22:24.56,Default,,0,0,0,,which is what happens to some lost souls resist, which is what happens to some lost
Dialogue: 0,1:22:24.77,1:22:26.17,Default,,0,0,0,,souls.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:26.17,1:22:33.76,Default,,0,0,0,,You walk through endless dimensions almost through eternity and never to return
Dialogue: 0,1:22:33.96,1:22:38.94,Default,,0,0,0,,to spiritual truth as it is, each dimension has its own God,
Dialogue: 0,1:22:39.14,1:22:45.69,Default,,0,0,0,,its own hierarchy, its own celebrities, its own rules and regulations.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:45.89,1:22:55.73,Default,,0,0,0,,So spiritual tradition says it is not it isn't that there are no such dimensions.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:55.93,1:22:56.92,Default,,0,0,0,,There are.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:57.11,1:22:59.11,Default,,0,0,0,,But wisdom teaches.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:59.11,1:23:00.81,Default,,0,0,0,,It teaches not to go there.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:01.01,1:23:03.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Why? Because you're not equipped to go there.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:03.52,1:23:06.60,Default,,0,0,0,,You're not equipped for those dimensions.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:06.81,1:23:10.77,Default,,0,0,0,,If you're equipped for those dimensions, you wouldn't be here as a human.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:10.97,1:23:15.35,Default,,0,0,0,,You would be there as a woo woo
Dialogue: 0,1:23:15.56,1:23:19.22,Default,,0,0,0,,following the great God,
Dialogue: 0,1:23:19.42,1:23:26.01,Default,,0,0,0,,who, if you prostrate yourself, will drive across you on wheels.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:26.21,1:23:31.13,Default,,0,0,0,,There's all kinds of channel books tell you about all these dimensions.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:31.32,1:23:34.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore, I think it's best to avoid
Dialogue: 0,1:23:34.68,1:23:36.25,Default,,0,0,0,,channel books. OK.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:36.44,1:23:40.50,Default,,0,0,0,,It's best to avoid channel books resist.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:40.69,1:23:41.10,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:41.30,1:23:45.57,Default,,0,0,0,,For the spiritual safety, then, is the first thing that we're interested in.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:45.77,1:23:47.46,Default,,0,0,0,,It isn't that they're not correct.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:47.65,1:23:49.46,Default,,0,0,0,,It isn't that they may not be true.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:49.65,1:23:56.06,Default,,0,0,0,,It's just that the spiritual tradition says it's not wise to go there.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:56.27,1:23:57.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Not wise to go there.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:58.18,1:24:04.39,Default,,0,0,0,,I got lost in the desert one time and I realized it was not wise to go where I was.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:05.39,1:24:06.35,Default,,0,0,0,,No road back.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:06.35,1:24:09.50,Default,,0,0,0,,No way of knowing where there was a road
Dialogue: 0,1:24:09.69,1:24:12.10,Default,,0,0,0,,and the truck was out of water and I was out of water.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:12.30,1:24:15.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, so do not go there.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:15.85,1:24:17.69,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:18.69,1:24:21.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Non egoistic teachers are respected
Dialogue: 0,1:24:22.06,1:24:26.65,Default,,0,0,0,,because their intention is educational, it's self-supporting.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:26.85,1:24:30.61,Default,,0,0,0,,We never solicit and never ask for donations or anything like this.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:30.81,1:24:32.67,Default,,0,0,0,,It's freestanding
Dialogue: 0,1:24:32.86,1:24:37.06,Default,,0,0,0,,and devoid of induced or altered states of consciousness.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:37.50,1:24:39.85,Default,,0,0,0,,You can induce these states by all kinds
Dialogue: 0,1:24:40.06,1:24:50.22,Default,,0,0,0,,of breathing exercises, postures, diets, invoking of other entities, etc.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:50.43,1:24:55.35,Default,,0,0,0,,That's not going to take you to enlightenment, at least not in this lifetime.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:55.55,1:24:59.43,Default,,0,0,0,,So this advice is of the highest order.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:59.63,1:25:00.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Resist. All right.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:00.75,1:25:02.67,Default,,0,0,0,,That advice is of the highest order.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:02.86,1:25:05.59,Default,,0,0,0,,So, OK, we didn't say not to do it.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:05.78,1:25:07.82,Default,,0,0,0,,We just said it's not going to serve the highest order.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:08.02,1:25:08.85,Default,,0,0,0,,OK.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:09.14,1:25:10.65,Default,,0,0,0,,People who have followed the highest
Dialogue: 0,1:25:10.85,1:25:16.77,Default,,0,0,0,,order of things have over time been confirmably enlightened.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:16.97,1:25:21.64,Default,,0,0,0,,And so this is a rather well-known list of spiritual teachers.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:21.85,1:25:23.77,Default,,0,0,0,,I think we repeated it again in the newest
Dialogue: 0,1:25:23.97,1:25:28.25,Default,,0,0,0,,book so that people don't have to go back and refer to some previous book.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:28.44,1:25:31.18,Default,,0,0,0,,And these are very
Dialogue: 0,1:25:31.38,1:25:35.65,Default,,0,0,0,,no matter how many we list, somebody will always send me in the mail at least once
Dialogue: 0,1:25:35.85,1:25:39.77,Default,,0,0,0,,a week, I've given them 100 people that are calibrated.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:39.77,1:25:40.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Integrous.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:40.81,1:25:46.09,Default,,0,0,0,,And they'll say, what about Nook Nook Bomba in Bombay?
Dialogue: 0,1:25:46.28,1:25:49.36,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll say, you got 100 teachers, isn't that good enough?
Dialogue: 0,1:25:49.56,1:25:52.72,Default,,0,0,0,,You got to find Nook Nook Bomba.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:52.93,1:25:55.89,Default,,0,0,0,,It's got to find some weird cat someplace.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:56.09,1:25:58.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Not that that person couldn't be so.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:59.09,1:26:02.97,Default,,0,0,0,,But it just always boggles my mind
Dialogue: 0,1:26:03.17,1:26:06.52,Default,,0,0,0,,what a person will go to to avoid the obvious.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:06.72,1:26:10.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Why? Because these just sound mundane and what they like is something
Dialogue: 0,1:26:11.13,1:26:12.40,Default,,0,0,0,,that's wild and crazy.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:12.60,1:26:15.40,Default,,0,0,0,,All kinds of Arabian robes on and spooky
Dialogue: 0,1:26:15.60,1:26:20.52,Default,,0,0,0,,postures and wild dances and things like this.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:22.72,1:26:26.89,Default,,0,0,0,,And these people just sound like hard work, you know,
Dialogue: 0,1:26:27.09,1:26:29.42,Default,,0,0,0,,instead of all the fancy dancing.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:29.61,1:26:31.85,Default,,0,0,0,,All right. So these are very well-known teachers
Dialogue: 0,1:26:32.06,1:26:35.85,Default,,0,0,0,,over time, and we've calibrated them all to very reliable lists.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:36.06,1:26:40.02,Default,,0,0,0,,And these are all names that everyone here recognizes.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:40.22,1:26:47.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Swami Buddha, Nanda, Eric Butterworth, John Calvin, Confucius,
Dialogue: 0,1:26:47.57,1:26:51.81,Default,,0,0,0,,the Dalai Lama currently living.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:54.00,1:26:55.47,Default,,0,0,0,,So these are the great names.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:55.68,1:27:00.68,Default,,0,0,0,,They calibrate up into the seven hundreds, six hundreds, all the great names.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:00.88,1:27:05.78,Default,,0,0,0,,And many of these we have tried to visit them at times when they were available
Dialogue: 0,1:27:05.98,1:27:10.35,Default,,0,0,0,,and meet them if we could, you know, the current pope.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:10.35,1:27:14.86,Default,,0,0,0,,And so you don't have to be Catholic
Dialogue: 0,1:27:15.06,1:27:20.18,Default,,0,0,0,,to realize that the pope has follows some kind of spiritual discipline
Dialogue: 0,1:27:20.39,1:27:25.75,Default,,0,0,0,,and is answerable to God to the best of his own intention.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:25.94,1:27:27.98,Default,,0,0,0,,It's five hundred and seventy.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:28.18,1:27:29.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Five hundred seventy is very integrous.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:30.18,1:27:35.10,Default,,0,0,0,,And I think the Dalai Lama also calibrates around 570.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:35.31,1:27:40.46,Default,,0,0,0,,So that's about the highest you can reach and still function in the world.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:40.65,1:27:44.57,Default,,0,0,0,,And beyond 570, there wouldn't be any interest
Dialogue: 0,1:27:44.77,1:27:47.26,Default,,0,0,0,,in functioning as the head of a world church.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:47.46,1:27:50.97,Default,,0,0,0,,You see, that's a whole different dimension.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:51.18,1:27:55.43,Default,,0,0,0,,So the mystic is not interested in
Dialogue: 0,1:27:55.64,1:28:00.88,Default,,0,0,0,,running a church or a big spiritual organization.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:01.07,1:28:02.15,Default,,0,0,0,,For instance, A.A.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:02.35,1:28:07.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Bill Wilson calibrated around 570, and
Dialogue: 0,1:28:07.61,1:28:11.50,Default,,0,0,0,,he spiritually energized the 12-step movement.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:11.69,1:28:13.73,Default,,0,0,0,,But it wasn't run by him.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:13.93,1:28:15.93,Default,,0,0,0,,And he left eventually, of course.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:16.14,1:28:21.65,Default,,0,0,0,,And so it runs by virtue of the truth of its own spiritual reality.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:21.85,1:28:28.65,Default,,0,0,0,,The 12-step groups calibrate around 540, which is the energy of healing.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:28.85,1:28:34.53,Default,,0,0,0,,So healing begins to spontaneously take place in the presence of the 12-step groups.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:34.73,1:28:39.42,Default,,0,0,0,,So the 12-step groups we speak very highly of because
Dialogue: 0,1:28:39.61,1:28:41.42,Default,,0,0,0,,they're devoid of work.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:41.69,1:28:44.14,Default,,0,0,0,,They're devoid of worldliness and materiality.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:44.34,1:28:45.89,Default,,0,0,0,,So we'll go on to the next one.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:46.10,1:28:49.98,Default,,0,0,0,,It says, these are all the well-known teachers.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:50.18,1:28:52.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, has anybody got anybody on their mind?
Dialogue: 0,1:28:52.86,1:28:56.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyone calibrated who isn't up there?
Dialogue: 0,1:28:56.92,1:29:00.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,1:29:00.89,1:29:07.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Oprah, 500.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:08.10,1:29:09.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Oprah's about 500.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:09.71,1:29:12.52,Default,,0,0,0,,She's very, very up there.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:12.72,1:29:13.89,Default,,0,0,0,,But she's not 540.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:14.09,1:29:18.71,Default,,0,0,0,,She hasn't reached Sainte-Wood yet.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:18.90,1:29:20.43,Default,,0,0,0,,She's integrous and loving.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:20.59,1:29:22.26,Default,,0,0,0,,She's integrous and loving.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:22.46,1:29:27.31,Default,,0,0,0,,And I've spoken to her.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:27.52,1:29:34.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Babaji is a fantasy.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:35.11,1:29:37.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Babaji is a fantasy.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:37.57,1:29:39.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Babaji calibrates a minus.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:39.30,1:29:46.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Supposedly lived alive for 500 years in the Himalayas and all this crap.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:46.73,1:29:50.57,Default,,0,0,0,,And I saw all kinds of negative effects of the belief in Babaji.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:50.77,1:29:52.50,Default,,0,0,0,,And Babaji's
Dialogue: 0,1:29:53.69,1:29:58.61,Default,,0,0,0,,people were coming in, you know, they got orders from Babaji that the world was coming to an end.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:58.81,1:30:05.38,Default,,0,0,0,,New York City was going to break under 14th Street and California was going to drop off in the ocean.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:05.57,1:30:08.02,Default,,0,0,0,,And that was all Babaji.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:08.22,1:30:10.02,Default,,0,0,0,,There is no such entity as Babaji.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:10.22,1:30:13.47,Default,,0,0,0,,It's pure BS.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:13.68,1:30:30.27,Default,,0,0,0,,You may quote me, but I never heard of such a person.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:30.47,1:30:33.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Eckhart, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:33.50,1:30:42.48,Default,,0,0,0,,We don't want to do Eckhart, no.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:42.68,1:30:45.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, we've taught you all how to do this yourself.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:50.14,1:30:53.82,Default,,0,0,0,,The trouble with contemporary authors and all is people have their favorites.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:54.02,1:30:55.47,Default,,0,0,0,,And then, if you don't say
Dialogue: 0,1:30:55.67,1:30:58.14,Default,,0,0,0,,something favorable, they're going to get on their blog.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:58.35,1:31:02.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Everybody's got to get on their blog, you know, have a couple more drinks.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:02.92,1:31:05.52,Default,,0,0,0,,And I guess we'll tell that holy guy where to go.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:05.72,1:31:07.07,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean,
Dialogue: 0,1:31:08.19,1:31:10.00,Default,,0,0,0,,we'll tell that Hawkins guy where to go.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:10.19,1:31:10.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:11.15,1:31:12.84,Default,,0,0,0,,I have another drink in here.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:13.03,1:31:18.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, if you, you dumbass, you dumbass.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:18.72,1:31:24.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Some of the blogs we get, I'll tell you, it's really embarrassing to be a human being.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:25.14,1:31:27.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Get to heaven. Are you from a human being?
Dialogue: 0,1:31:27.77,1:31:28.26,Default,,0,0,0,,No, no.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:28.85,1:31:31.75,Default,,0,0,0,,You look like one.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:31.94,1:31:34.55,Default,,0,0,0,,I was there long enough to study them there.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:34.75,1:31:35.98,Default,,0,0,0,,And
Dialogue: 0,1:31:42.40,1:31:47.31,Default,,0,0,0,,the ill will that comes across is sometimes just absolutely mind boggling.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:47.52,1:31:53.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Some former president's wife is in a serious area, falling down half dead.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:53.19,1:31:54.86,Default,,0,0,0,,What was her name?
Dialogue: 0,1:31:55.06,1:31:56.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Nancy. Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:56.39,1:32:00.98,Default,,0,0,0,,So the blog sites are wishing she would die suffering and die soon.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:01.18,1:32:02.75,Default,,0,0,0,,I thought, you know, I can't.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:02.94,1:32:04.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Imagine such malevolence.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:04.67,1:32:08.22,Default,,0,0,0,,And we're supposed to hold this up and die for free speech.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:08.42,1:32:10.81,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm supposed to die for this idiot to get
Dialogue: 0,1:32:11.02,1:32:15.85,Default,,0,0,0,,on the blog site and say a thing about Nancy Reagan, such as was said,
Dialogue: 0,1:32:16.06,1:32:23.03,Default,,0,0,0,,which I wouldn't say about anybody, much less somebody like the Reagan lady.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:23.23,1:32:28.93,Default,,0,0,0,,So the downside of free speech is that if you don't
Dialogue: 0,1:32:29.14,1:32:34.14,Default,,0,0,0,,honor it and keep it within certain parameters, in the end, you will lose it.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:34.26,1:32:35.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Isn't that right, George?
Dialogue: 0,1:32:36.06,1:32:39.03,Default,,0,0,0,,What George sent me something this week.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:39.23,1:32:43.44,Default,,0,0,0,,What was that a quote from two days ago?
Dialogue: 0,1:32:43.64,1:32:46.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, two days ago.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:46.21,1:32:49.00,Default,,0,0,0,,That's forever ago in his life.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:49.19,1:32:51.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway, he sent me something
Dialogue: 0,1:32:52.15,1:32:55.56,Default,,0,0,0,,that was very interesting, that those who don't revere
Dialogue: 0,1:32:55.76,1:33:01.36,Default,,0,0,0,,and don't hold to ethics and morality will soon lose their freedom.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:01.56,1:33:06.21,Default,,0,0,0,,So the downside of freedom of speech is that, you know, it's a two edged sword.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:06.85,1:33:09.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Freedom of speech is a two edged sword.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:09.30,1:33:13.36,Default,,0,0,0,,And people don't realize it's two edged, not just one edged.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:13.56,1:33:17.35,Default,,0,0,0,,It's two edged that you can cut your
Dialogue: 0,1:33:17.55,1:33:21.97,Default,,0,0,0,,opponent, but you can also kill yourself with the same weapon.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:22.18,1:33:27.26,Default,,0,0,0,,So free speech will kill somebody, yourself or somebody else,
Dialogue: 0,1:33:27.46,1:33:31.73,Default,,0,0,0,,unless integrity and morality is used within the limitations of integrity
Dialogue: 0,1:33:31.93,1:33:34.53,Default,,0,0,0,,and morality, ethics and responsibility.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:34.73,1:33:37.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah. All right.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:37.22,1:33:37.73,Default,,0,0,0,,So.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:37.93,1:33:39.42,Default,,0,0,0,,That's enough lecturing for today.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:39.61,1:33:44.47,Default,,0,0,0,,So Pope Paul, et cetera, is 570.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:44.67,1:33:48.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Father Peale performed miracles.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:48.55,1:33:53.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Wang Po was one of my old heroes.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:54.02,1:33:57.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Wang Po was one of my old heroes.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:57.27,1:34:00.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Wang Po followed the pathway of negation,
Dialogue: 0,1:34:00.71,1:34:04.38,Default,,0,0,0,,which I myself followed for some lifetimes, actually.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:04.57,1:34:06.06,Default,,0,0,0,,And
Dialogue: 0,1:34:08.68,1:34:10.17,Default,,0,0,0,,it negates
Dialogue: 0,1:34:10.36,1:34:13.77,Default,,0,0,0,,it's the pathway of negation, not this, not that.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:13.97,1:34:17.93,Default,,0,0,0,,The difficulty with the pathway of negation, as we said before,
Dialogue: 0,1:34:18.14,1:34:20.53,Default,,0,0,0,,is it will eventually take you to the void.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:20.73,1:34:26.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Eventually it will take you to an infinite and very impressive space.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:26.27,1:34:32.43,Default,,0,0,0,,If you negate everything that can be said or conceptualized as truth,
Dialogue: 0,1:34:32.63,1:34:40.71,Default,,0,0,0,,you will get rid of a lot of falsehood to the aphorisms that have to do with
Dialogue: 0,1:34:40.82,1:34:43.77,Default,,0,0,0,,negating all conceptual thought.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:43.97,1:34:49.65,Default,,0,0,0,,So Wang Po taught to let go of all conceptual thought.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:49.85,1:34:58.76,Default,,0,0,0,,The difficulty is that you end up in the infinite void where Wang Po himself landed.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:58.96,1:35:04.14,Default,,0,0,0,,All right. Oh, I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:04.34,1:35:06.50,Default,,0,0,0,,It's going to fill in with that. I didn't know.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:06.69,1:35:08.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, no, we'll have a few minutes.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:08.77,1:35:14.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway, Wang Po, which we've described before, I myself had been into a very
Dialogue: 0,1:35:14.36,1:35:19.39,Default,,0,0,0,,deeply infinite space and the infinite space in which I
Dialogue: 0,1:35:19.60,1:35:25.73,Default,,0,0,0,,came out spontaneously was a field of infinite love beyond description.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:25.93,1:35:32.65,Default,,0,0,0,,The totality of nonlinear, the presence eliminated all sense of a personal self,
Dialogue: 0,1:35:32.85,1:35:36.18,Default,,0,0,0,,all beginning or endings, all sense of time.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:36.38,1:35:39.06,Default,,0,0,0,,There was the realization of the divinity
Dialogue: 0,1:35:39.26,1:35:44.57,Default,,0,0,0,,of the essence of one's own existence, the self with a capital S, which shines forth
Dialogue: 0,1:35:44.77,1:35:48.60,Default,,0,0,0,,as infinite love, timeless beyond all dimension.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:48.81,1:35:51.28,Default,,0,0,0,,So that which I am in reality,
Dialogue: 0,1:35:51.48,1:35:56.90,Default,,0,0,0,,experience infinite foreverness of infinite lovingness.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:57.10,1:36:01.94,Default,,0,0,0,,So in fact, following the pathway of negation again in this lifetime,
Dialogue: 0,1:36:02.14,1:36:09.93,Default,,0,0,0,,I again ended up in the negative in the in the nonlinear domain of the void at nine
Dialogue: 0,1:36:10.13,1:36:15.18,Default,,0,0,0,,level 960 and realized the error, I realized the error because the
Dialogue: 0,1:36:15.51,1:36:18.73,Default,,0,0,0,,infinite field of infinite love was not there.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:18.93,1:36:21.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore, I rejected it and went back
Dialogue: 0,1:36:21.97,1:36:28.52,Default,,0,0,0,,and retraced my steps and reemerged into what I had experienced before.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:28.72,1:36:34.97,Default,,0,0,0,,So the ultimate state is one of infinite lovingness, not avoidance.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:35.18,1:36:38.89,Default,,0,0,0,,So the void is impressive.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:39.09,1:36:43.47,Default,,0,0,0,,The void is extremely impressive, extremely impressive.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:43.68,1:36:46.15,Default,,0,0,0,,But it is what's missing is
Dialogue: 0,1:36:46.35,1:36:47.64,Default,,0,0,0,,the love of God.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:47.84,1:36:54.15,Default,,0,0,0,,So no spiritual state is complete without the presence then of an infinite field
Dialogue: 0,1:36:54.35,1:36:57.60,Default,,0,0,0,,of love, which illuminates everything.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:57.80,1:37:02.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Everything is illuminated because the essence of all existence is divinity,
